Are you Mr. Aaron?

15
00:05:38,674 --> 00:05:40,765
Yeah, that's right.
Come on.

16
00:05:44,478 --> 00:05:45,749
I don't suppose--

17
00:05:46,640 --> 00:05:48,545
Well, I don't suppose
I'll be very good at this.

18
00:05:48,546 --> 00:05:49,626
Well, nobody is.

19
00:05:49,627 --> 00:05:51,343
The important thing is
to get in the photograph.

20
00:05:51,344 --> 00:05:52,297
Ever been
to Brighton before?

21
00:05:52,298 --> 00:05:53,229
Brighton, no.

22
00:05:53,283 --> 00:05:54,712
I've had to change
the hotel.

23
00:05:54,713 --> 00:05:55,699
Change the hotel?
Why? What's happened?

24
00:05:55,700 --> 00:05:57,003
Well, it's just
the other place got raided

25
00:05:57,004 --> 00:05:58,526
a couple
of nights ago--

26
00:05:58,527 --> 00:05:59,047
Raided?

27
00:05:59,863 --> 00:06:00,912
It's all right.
It's all right.

28
00:06:00,913 --> 00:06:02,310
I got us booked
at the Radley Hotel.

29
00:06:02,311 --> 00:06:03,201
It's a much
better place.

30
00:06:03,202 --> 00:06:04,567
It's going to cost
a little bit more,

31
00:06:04,568 --> 00:06:05,428
that's all.

32
00:06:06,189 --> 00:06:08,097
We'll go up to my office first,

33
00:06:08,098 --> 00:06:10,099
and I'll tell you
how it all works.

34
00:06:10,100 --> 00:06:12,881
Don't look so worried.
It'll be fine.

35
00:06:25,105 --> 00:06:26,855
Is everything
all right?

36
00:06:41,855 --> 00:06:44,245
Nothing seems
to have been taken.

37
00:06:46,243 --> 00:06:47,513
What do you do
for a living,

38
00:06:47,514 --> 00:06:48,911
if you don't mind
my asking?

39
00:06:48,912 --> 00:06:51,173
Do? I'm a lawyer,
a barrister.

40
00:06:53,140 --> 00:06:54,191
Ah...barrister.

41
00:06:55,461 --> 00:06:58,552
Yeah, I thought it was
something like that.

42
00:07:00,801 --> 00:07:02,073
You see her
down there?

43
00:07:02,074 --> 00:07:03,310
Well, that's
your woman.

44
00:07:03,311 --> 00:07:04,869
I can't walk
into a hotel with her.

45
00:07:04,870 --> 00:07:07,730
Yeah, you see, I was
totally misinformed

46
00:07:08,778 --> 00:07:10,528
about the type of
gentleman you were, sir.

47
00:07:10,529 --> 00:07:13,070
No. No, I... can't.
I just can't.

48
00:07:13,232 --> 00:07:13,923
Mm-hmm...

49
00:07:16,314 --> 00:07:18,253
Perhaps-- Perhaps I could
talk to my wife.

50
00:07:18,254 --> 00:07:19,005
Your wife?

51
00:07:19,207 --> 00:07:20,887
Yeah, she's an actress.

52
00:07:21,210 --> 00:07:23,466
I mean, she's never done
anything like this before.

53
00:07:23,467 --> 00:07:25,148
Do you think she might?

54
00:07:25,659 --> 00:07:29,191
I mean, I-- if it's--
I could pay more, I mean.

55
00:07:43,749 --> 00:07:45,751
Uh, good evening,
my name is--

56
00:07:45,752 --> 00:07:47,402
I have a double
room booked.

57
00:07:47,403 --> 00:07:48,357
What name, sir?

58
00:07:48,358 --> 00:07:49,578
Uh, er, Franklin.

59
00:07:50,742 --> 00:07:52,075
It's a double room.

60
00:07:52,076 --> 00:07:54,396
I booked it
about two days ago.

61
00:07:55,192 --> 00:07:57,287
If you'd like
to sign in here, sir.

62
00:07:57,288 --> 00:07:58,279
[BELL RINGING]

63
00:07:59,515 --> 00:08:00,469
Thank you very much.

64
00:08:00,470 --> 00:08:01,169
[KNOCKING]

65
00:08:02,249 --> 00:08:04,887
You developed a sudden interest
in hotel architecture?

66
00:08:04,888 --> 00:08:05,699
Hey, Frank.

67
00:08:06,318 --> 00:08:08,478
Hope you're not doing
any illegal divorce work.

68
00:08:08,479 --> 00:08:10,099
I'm tailing a suspect here.

69
