74
00:08:19,128 --> 00:08:20,654
Hey, it's Christmas,
you miserable sod.

75
00:08:20,655 --> 00:08:21,465
Come round.

76
00:08:29,490 --> 00:08:30,921
Would you like a drink, sir?

77
00:08:30,922 --> 00:08:33,182
A drink?
Um, no... not for me.

78
00:08:33,942 --> 00:08:35,693
Would you like something?

79
00:08:37,598 --> 00:08:39,058
The usual... darling.

80
00:08:41,952 --> 00:08:42,653
Champagne.

81
00:08:43,192 --> 00:08:44,302
Oh, champagne...

82
00:08:45,895 --> 00:08:46,885
Uh, champagne.

83
00:08:51,773 --> 00:08:53,274
You can smile a bit.

84
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:55,748
Order a prawn cocktail

85
00:08:55,749 --> 00:08:57,305
and pretend you're trying
to impress me.

86
00:08:57,306 --> 00:08:58,766
Impress you... right.

87
00:09:00,581 --> 00:09:02,106
I'm not very keen
on champagne,

88
00:09:02,107 --> 00:09:02,966
that's all.

89
00:09:12,503 --> 00:09:14,824
Denny! The man
I wanted to see.

90
00:09:15,045 --> 00:09:16,124
Give us
the car keys.

91
00:09:16,125 --> 00:09:17,842
Why? Didn't Bob bring
the money round to you--

92
00:09:17,843 --> 00:09:19,588
Look, don't start,
just give us the keys. Now.

93
00:09:19,589 --> 00:09:20,279
Ah, for--

94
00:09:26,807 --> 00:09:27,950
Look, it's good faith,
isn't it?

95
00:09:27,951 --> 00:09:28,761
Yeah, yeah.

96
00:09:28,839 --> 00:09:30,301
We had a deal,
and I've seen nothing.

97
00:09:30,302 --> 00:09:32,178
I know. I know.
Bob promised me 200 quid.

98
00:09:32,179 --> 00:09:34,086
He said he'd bring 20 quid
round to your house--

99
00:09:34,087 --> 00:09:36,023
Yeah, but you're months
behind with the payments.

100
00:09:36,024 --> 00:09:37,264
I know. I'm sorry.

101
00:09:37,265 --> 00:09:38,599
Look. Look, we agreed
terms, didn't we?

102
00:09:38,600 --> 00:09:39,531
Yeah... Yeah.

103
00:09:42,065 --> 00:09:44,035
Well, don't make me
feel bad about it.

104
00:09:44,036 --> 00:09:45,559
All right, all right,
Denny, listen to me.

105
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:46,896
If the money's
not on your desk

106
00:09:46,897 --> 00:09:48,072
9:00 tomorrow morning,

107
00:09:48,073 --> 00:09:49,583
keep the car forever.

108
00:09:49,790 --> 00:09:50,240
9:00.

109
00:10:03,363 --> 00:10:03,883
Well...

110
00:10:04,889 --> 00:10:07,430
So what do we--
what do I do now?

111
00:10:08,449 --> 00:10:11,180
I'll go into
the bathroom and change.

112
00:10:11,438 --> 00:10:13,184
Knock on the door
when you're ready.

113
00:10:13,185 --> 00:10:15,856
Knock on the door
when I'm... ready.

114
00:10:22,786 --> 00:10:24,367
[CLOCK CHIMES MIDNIGHT]

115
00:10:25,201 --> 00:10:26,242
There you are.

116
00:10:54,352 --> 00:10:55,303
Excuse me, dear,

117
00:10:55,304 --> 00:10:56,606
could you open
46 for me, please?

118
00:10:56,607 --> 00:10:57,818
I forgot my key.

119
00:10:58,007 --> 00:10:58,757
Thank you.

120
00:11:04,747 --> 00:11:06,906
[WHISPERING]
You're a witness.

121
00:11:12,296 --> 00:11:15,156
You two should be
ashamed of yourselves.

122
00:11:17,381 --> 00:11:18,422
Uh, excuse me?

123
00:11:20,210 --> 00:11:21,371
Excuse me, miss?

124
00:11:29,173 --> 00:11:30,743
Remember what you saw.

125
00:11:32,640 --> 00:11:34,099
How much did you get?

126
00:11:34,100 --> 00:11:34,440
$25.

127
00:11:35,055 --> 00:11:35,685
Show me.

128
00:11:36,008 --> 00:11:37,344
I had some debts
to pay back.

129
00:11:37,345 --> 00:11:38,678
So you've paid
the rent, did you?

130
00:11:38,679 --> 00:11:39,960
You lying bastard.

131
00:11:40,268 --> 00:11:41,570
How much do
we owe now?

132
00:11:41,571 --> 00:11:43,482
Give it a rest,
will you?

133
00:11:43,575 --> 00:11:47,406
Well, I didn't marry you
to live in a bloody office.

134
00:12:07,988 --> 00:12:09,848
Hey, hey.
Close the door.

135
00:12:11,422 --> 00:12:12,463
Whose is this?

136
00:12:13,487 --> 00:12:13,887
What?

137
00:12:17,239 --> 00:12:19,272
You've been with someone else,
haven't you?

138
00:12:19,273 --> 00:12:21,073
Oh, Christ,
stop it. No.

139
00:12:21,625 --> 00:12:22,316
You liar.

140
00:12:22,579 --> 00:12:24,676
A client must have dropped it.

141
00:12:24,677 --> 00:12:25,692
You're so damned suspicious.

142
00:12:25,693 --> 00:12:27,219
Because you never change.

143
00:12:27,220 --> 00:12:28,966
You're the one wanted
to get married, sweetheart,

144
00:12:28,967 --> 00:12:29,538
not me.

145
00:12:30,050 --> 00:12:32,030
Now, close
the bloody door.

146
00:12:58,532 --> 00:12:59,802
Get out of there.

147
00:13:01,107 --> 00:13:02,097
Mr. Dangerous.

148
00:13:04,318 --> 00:13:05,715
Where did you
get this from?

149
00:13:05,716 --> 00:13:07,431
A friend of mine
brought it back from Italy.

150
00:13:07,432 --> 00:13:08,993
Come on,
give me it.

151
00:13:09,499 --> 00:13:11,659
He said it belonged
to Mussolini.

152
00:13:13,121 --> 00:13:13,752
Come on.

153
00:13:14,458 --> 00:13:15,438
Is it loaded?

154
00:13:15,602 --> 00:13:16,413
Yeah, sure.

155
00:13:16,557 --> 00:13:18,177
Of course it's loaded.

156
00:13:18,208 --> 00:13:18,608
Bang!

157
00:13:21,516 --> 00:13:23,103
Don't worry
about going to court,

158
00:13:23,104 --> 00:13:24,024
that's easy.

159
00:13:24,154 --> 00:13:25,202
We just need
the photograph

160
00:13:25,203 --> 00:13:26,568
and the night porter
or a chambermaid

161
00:13:26,569 --> 00:13:27,583
to act as a witness.

162
00:13:27,584 --> 00:13:29,301
I mean, they might
send someone to the hotel

163
00:13:29,302 --> 00:13:30,638
to check out
that you were seen,

164
00:13:30,639 --> 00:13:31,592
but they'll be
no problems.

165
00:13:31,593 --> 00:13:33,103
I sincerely hope not.

166
00:13:33,147 --> 00:13:33,487
Hey!

167
00:13:35,693 --> 00:13:36,033
Hey!

168
00:13:41,096 --> 00:13:43,477
Hey, that's my car,
you bastard!

169
00:13:43,672 --> 00:13:44,302
Get out!

170
00:13:46,215 --> 00:13:47,867
Tony,
get out the car.

171
00:13:47,868 --> 00:13:49,137
Come on! Get out!

172
00:13:51,745 --> 00:13:53,717
I won his car in a poker game,
you know?

173
00:13:53,718 --> 00:13:54,698
What a loser.

174
00:14:13,489 --> 00:14:16,600
* ...To spend Christmas
On Christmas Island *

175
00:14:18,671 --> 00:14:21,149
* How'd you like
To hang your stocking *

176
00:14:21,150 --> 00:14:23,421
* On a great big coconut tree? *

177
00:14:24,774 --> 00:14:26,214
Time to go to work.

178
00:14:26,458 --> 00:14:30,589
* How'd you like to stay up late
Like the islanders do? *

179
00:14:32,721 --> 00:14:34,691
* Wait for Santa to sail in

180
00:14:35,868 --> 00:14:38,439
* With your presents
In a canoe... *

181
00:14:44,132 --> 00:14:45,721
That's it
at the far end,

182
00:14:45,722 --> 00:14:46,532
over there.

183
00:14:51,540 --> 00:14:52,619
So keep near me.

184
00:14:52,620 --> 00:14:54,601
Remember,
you're a witness.

185
00:14:56,975 --> 00:14:59,835
You two should be
ashamed of yourselves.

186
00:15:00,248 --> 00:15:00,888
[SCREAMS]

187
00:15:21,038 --> 00:15:23,326
Okay, just take
everybody's names,

188
00:15:23,327 --> 00:15:25,107
keep the guests
in their rooms for the moment,

189
00:15:25,108 --> 00:15:27,149
just make sure nobody leaves.

190
00:15:39,508 --> 00:15:40,839
Are you all right?

191
00:15:45,039 --> 00:15:46,200
Get some coffee.

192
00:15:46,693 --> 00:15:48,364
I need to talk to you.

193
00:15:55,689 --> 00:15:58,070
Were you in the bar
all evening?

194
00:15:59,852 --> 00:16:01,363
Did you see anything?

195
00:16:02,037 --> 00:16:02,667
Oh, God.

196
00:16:03,373 --> 00:16:05,277
I can't believe
this has happened.

197
00:16:05,278 --> 00:16:06,489
I just saw her--

198
00:16:06,934 --> 00:16:07,981
What are you doing?

199
00:16:07,982 --> 00:16:09,221
Well, you touched
the door handle,

200
00:16:09,222 --> 00:16:10,082
didn't you?

201
00:16:10,174 --> 00:16:11,127
Oh, I'm sorry.
I forgot.

202
00:16:11,128 --> 00:16:12,081
Well, you're fine.

203
00:16:12,082 --> 00:16:13,417
I guess you can
do your own.

204
00:16:13,418 --> 00:16:14,594
No. Do it
for me, Frank.

205
00:16:14,595 --> 00:16:16,658
My hands are
shaking too much.

206
00:16:16,659 --> 00:16:17,803
Did you book
the room for them?

207
00:16:17,804 --> 00:16:18,205
Yeah.

208
00:16:18,727 --> 00:16:20,348
Why did you put them
on the top floor?

209
00:16:20,349 --> 00:16:21,300
I don't know.

210
00:16:21,301 --> 00:16:22,476
If you wanted them
to be noticed,

211
00:16:22,477 --> 00:16:24,161
you'd stick them in the middle
of the first floor--

212
00:16:24,162 --> 00:16:25,147
I don't know, Frank, I'm sorry.

213
00:16:25,148 --> 00:16:26,576
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry.

214
00:16:26,577 --> 00:16:29,184
It's all right. Don't worry.

215
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:35,008
It's just a photograph.

216
00:16:35,009 --> 00:16:36,342
That's all it is.

217
00:16:44,961 --> 00:16:45,717
Oh, Jesus.

218
00:16:50,448 --> 00:16:53,013
What kind of casket
do you want, sir?

219
00:16:53,014 --> 00:16:53,832
Uh, casket.

220
00:16:54,908 --> 00:16:55,311
Uh...

221
00:16:57,700 --> 00:17:00,075
I-- I haven't--
I haven't got much money.

222
00:17:00,076 --> 00:17:02,601
You'd better make it
the cheapest.

223
00:17:02,674 --> 00:17:03,855
[ENGINE STARTING]

224
00:17:34,642 --> 00:17:35,699
Why so formal, Frank?

225
00:17:35,700 --> 00:17:37,081
Can we do this
in my office?

226
00:17:37,082 --> 00:17:38,622
I've got a lot
of pressure on me.

227
00:17:38,623 --> 00:17:40,097
It's got to
all be done right.

228
00:17:40,098 --> 00:17:41,479
You know
Dave Waterston,

229
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:42,857
he's been
working with me.

230
00:17:42,858 --> 00:17:44,494
I was Colin's partner.

231
00:17:45,235 --> 00:17:46,453
You remember Colin, Tony?

232
00:17:46,454 --> 00:17:47,993
Yes. I remember Colin.

233
00:17:47,994 --> 00:17:50,338
We're not here
to discuss that.

234
00:17:50,371 --> 00:17:51,652
Look, Frank,
I've already--

235
00:17:51,653 --> 00:17:53,513
There's no need to go
into all that again.

236
00:17:53,514 --> 00:17:55,101
We got your statement.

237
00:17:55,312 --> 00:17:58,746
You know who was killed
along with your wife, Tony?

238
00:17:58,747 --> 00:18:01,184
His name was, uh,
Paduin, Padouin.

239
00:18:01,185 --> 00:18:02,564
He was
an Italian salesman.

240
00:18:02,565 --> 00:18:04,362
I don't know much
else about him.

241
00:18:04,363 --> 00:18:07,123
You obviously
haven't read the newspapers.

242
00:18:07,124 --> 00:18:09,048
His real name
was Carlo Stasio,

243
00:18:09,049 --> 00:18:10,523
famous painter, rich.

244
00:18:11,521 --> 00:18:12,985
I mean, really rich.

245
00:18:13,348 --> 00:18:14,924
How did you meet him?

246
00:18:15,981 --> 00:18:18,204
I-- I didn't,
until that day.

247
00:18:19,126 --> 00:18:20,762
His, uh, his solicitor
came into the office

248
00:18:20,763 --> 00:18:22,106
about a month ago.

249
00:18:22,112 --> 00:18:24,134
He said that
they wanted to...

250
00:18:24,135 --> 00:18:25,095
remain discreet.

251
00:18:25,096 --> 00:18:26,893
In fact, he said
that Padouin--

252
00:18:26,894 --> 00:18:29,713
that Stasio
wanted to use a false name

253
00:18:30,007 --> 00:18:31,451
on the hotel registry.

254
00:18:31,452 --> 00:18:33,636
I said that was all right
as long as there were witnesses,

255
00:18:33,637 --> 00:18:35,044
you know,
to identify him in court.

256
00:18:35,045 --> 00:18:38,063
Now, why would a millionaire
go to a dogshit little agency

257
00:18:38,064 --> 00:18:38,882
like yours?

258
00:18:40,532 --> 00:18:41,979
Maybe he wanted
anonymity,

259
00:18:41,980 --> 00:18:43,322
seeing who he was.

260
00:18:43,393 --> 00:18:45,957
I mean, no big agency's going
to arrange adulteries anyway,

261
00:18:45,958 --> 00:18:46,657
are they?

262
00:18:47,211 --> 00:18:48,205
They're against the law.

263
00:18:48,206 --> 00:18:49,975
They certainly are, Tony.

264
00:18:51,382 --> 00:18:54,716
We're not going to be able
to cover that up.

265
00:18:56,103 --> 00:18:56,678
I know.

266
00:18:59,823 --> 00:19:01,812
You said you were
in the hotel bar all night.

267
00:19:01,813 --> 00:19:02,775
From about
10:00, yeah.

268
00:19:02,776 --> 00:19:03,740
Never left your seat.

269
00:19:03,741 --> 00:19:04,023
So?

270
00:19:05,025 --> 00:19:07,846
The barmaid said you went out
for about ten minutes

271
00:19:07,847 --> 00:19:09,420
just before
you went upstairs.

272
00:19:09,421 --> 00:19:10,899
Jesus, I went
to the toilet, right?

273
00:19:10,900 --> 00:19:12,059
No, no, no, no.

274
00:19:12,567 --> 00:19:13,593
You went upstairs
and did her,

275
00:19:13,594 --> 00:19:14,462
didn't you?

276
00:19:14,813 --> 00:19:16,224
They found your prints
all over the bed.

277
00:19:16,225 --> 00:19:19,387
Oh, fuck off.
Is that the best you can do?

278
00:19:20,397 --> 00:19:21,745
You owe people
a lot of money.

279
00:19:21,746 --> 00:19:22,708
So what?
I owe money.

280
00:19:22,709 --> 00:19:23,862
That's not
a crime, is it?

281
00:19:23,863 --> 00:19:25,114
It's an incentive
to commit crime.

282
00:19:25,115 --> 00:19:27,629
I'll pretend
you didn't say that.

283
00:19:27,715 --> 00:19:28,775
Pretend what
you like.

284
00:19:28,776 --> 00:19:31,835
You're not getting away
with murder again.

285
00:19:31,920 --> 00:19:33,800
All right, eh.
All right!

286
00:19:35,098 --> 00:19:35,733
Come on.

287
00:19:39,013 --> 00:19:40,064
Dave, shut up!

288
00:19:42,833 --> 00:19:44,006
Leave him alone.

289
00:19:49,479 --> 00:19:50,601
Well, ask him, Frank.

290
00:19:50,602 --> 00:19:51,530
Ask me what?

291
00:19:53,842 --> 00:19:55,124
Do you possess a gun?

292
00:19:55,125 --> 00:19:55,531
What?

293
00:19:57,018 --> 00:19:57,423
No...

294
00:19:59,460 --> 00:20:02,057
What, do you think
I killed my wife,

295
00:20:02,058 --> 00:20:03,788
and then I killed
a complete stranger as well?

296
00:20:03,789 --> 00:20:04,978
Does that make sense?

297
00:20:04,979 --> 00:20:06,229
Even to a fucking
monkey brain

298
00:20:06,230 --> 00:20:07,319
like you, Waterston?

299
00:20:07,320 --> 00:20:08,701
Nobody thinks
anything like that.

300
00:20:08,702 --> 00:20:11,752
If there's nothing else,
Frank, can I go?

301
00:20:13,868 --> 00:20:14,831
There is
one more thing.

302
00:20:14,832 --> 00:20:16,630
Have you talked
to anyone in the station

303
00:20:16,631 --> 00:20:17,923
about the autopsy?

304
00:20:18,810 --> 00:20:20,165
Whoever killed them

305
00:20:20,643 --> 00:20:23,752
also cut off Stasio's thumb
as a souvenir.

306
00:20:26,355 --> 00:20:27,172
Oh, Tony...

307
00:20:30,462 --> 00:20:31,583
Happy Christmas.

308
00:21:12,731 --> 00:21:13,695
What are you doing here?

309
00:21:13,696 --> 00:21:14,625
Same as you.

310
00:21:16,425 --> 00:21:17,881
So what's the news?

311
00:21:18,188 --> 00:21:19,067
Oh, nothing.

312
00:21:19,536 --> 00:21:21,013
Someone saw
a smart red car

313
00:21:21,014 --> 00:21:22,781
outside the back
of the hotel.

314
00:21:22,782 --> 00:21:24,003
That's about it.

315
00:21:26,501 --> 00:21:27,552
Stasio's wife.

316
00:21:37,029 --> 00:21:37,897
Who's that?

317
00:21:38,698 --> 00:21:39,860
I have no idea.

318
00:21:59,689 --> 00:22:00,517
Interesting.

319
00:22:00,717 --> 00:22:01,998
Just remember who's
doing the investigation,

320
00:22:01,999 --> 00:22:02,929
all right?
Absolutely.

321
00:22:02,930 --> 00:22:03,859
I'm serious.

322
00:22:03,925 --> 00:22:06,025
I can't have
you around me.

323
00:22:06,686 --> 00:22:08,220
[CHURCH BELLS TOLLING]

324
00:22:30,339 --> 00:22:32,458
Mrs. Stasio,
I'm Frank Vance,

325
00:22:32,459 --> 00:22:34,418
the Detective in charge
of the investigation.

326
00:22:34,419 --> 00:22:35,665
I'd like to offer
my condolences,

327
00:22:35,666 --> 00:22:37,785
and say that if there's anything
you'd like me to do--

328
00:22:37,786 --> 00:22:39,777
I'll tell you
what you can do.

329
00:22:39,778 --> 00:22:40,964
You can go
to my house--

330
00:22:40,965 --> 00:22:41,722
my house--

331
00:22:42,152 --> 00:22:43,722
and throw that
bitch, Angeline,

332
00:22:43,723 --> 00:22:44,533
out of it.

333
00:22:44,944 --> 00:22:45,409
Right.

334
00:22:46,388 --> 00:22:50,569
When might it be convenient
to talk to you, Mrs. Stasio...

335
00:22:53,352 --> 00:22:54,534
[SEAGULLS CAWING]

336
00:23:13,000 --> 00:23:13,461
<i>Speak.</i>

337
00:23:14,753 --> 00:23:16,314
I have a floral tribute
to deliver.

338
00:23:16,315 --> 00:23:17,459
<i>Drive down to
the front entrance</i>

339
00:23:17,460 --> 00:23:18,963
<i>and I'll collect it.</i>

340
00:23:24,377 --> 00:23:25,891
Drive down, she says.

341
00:23:44,167 --> 00:23:44,919
Thank you.

342
00:23:45,125 --> 00:23:46,276
I'll take that.

343
00:23:46,843 --> 00:23:49,236
I need to give it to the lady
of the house herself.

344
00:23:49,237 --> 00:23:51,688
I'm sorry. She's not at home
to visitors at the moment.

345
00:23:51,689 --> 00:23:53,407
She is at home.
I saw her come in.

346
00:23:53,408 --> 00:23:53,870
Sorry.

347
00:23:54,365 --> 00:23:55,298
Wait, please.

348
00:23:55,989 --> 00:23:58,266
Could you give her this, please?

349
00:24:03,159 --> 00:24:03,914
Thank you.

350
00:24:40,508 --> 00:24:42,707
I can't help you, I'm afraid.

351
00:24:43,570 --> 00:24:45,415
I haven't asked you
anything yet.

352
00:24:45,416 --> 00:24:45,817
Uh...

353
00:24:46,374 --> 00:24:47,597
Tony. Tony Aaron.

354
00:24:49,049 --> 00:24:50,005
Angeline White.

355
00:24:50,006 --> 00:24:51,598
I kind of expected
to see his wife.

356
00:24:51,599 --> 00:24:53,064
This is a family home,
isn't it?

357
00:24:53,065 --> 00:24:54,498
She doesn't live here anymore.

358
00:24:54,499 --> 00:24:56,093
I'm sorry
you've wasted a journey.

359
00:24:56,094 --> 00:24:58,197
Don't you want to find out
who killed him?

360
00:24:58,198 --> 00:24:59,118
Do you know?

361
00:25:00,044 --> 00:25:00,677
Not yet.

362
00:25:01,097 --> 00:25:02,847
Then why don't we leave that
to the police?

363
00:25:02,848 --> 00:25:03,708
Good day, Mr. Aaron.

364
00:25:03,709 --> 00:25:05,263
It's not a good day.

365
00:25:05,876 --> 00:25:07,440
Not for either of us.

366
00:25:09,160 --> 00:25:10,784
Don't you get frightened
here on your own

367
00:25:10,785 --> 00:25:12,636
in a big house like this?

368
00:25:13,556 --> 00:25:16,945
Only when people like you
say things like that.

369
00:25:18,751 --> 00:25:21,140
A Detective Inspector
Vance has arrived.

370
00:25:21,141 --> 00:25:24,262
Um, it might be better
if he doesn't see me.

371
00:25:24,263 --> 00:25:26,242
Do you have
a back entrance?

372
00:25:26,243 --> 00:25:29,851
We don't usually have a need
for a back entrance.

373
00:25:29,967 --> 00:25:31,020
If there's nothing else,

374
00:25:31,021 --> 00:25:32,578
then I'll
dismiss the--

375
00:25:32,579 --> 00:25:35,439
The wages
are in envelopes in the hall.

376
00:25:39,400 --> 00:25:42,046
What does Stasio
need the oxygen for?

377
00:25:42,047 --> 00:25:42,908
Was he ill?

378
00:25:46,286 --> 00:25:47,338
He thought he was ill.

379
00:25:47,339 --> 00:25:49,054
There was
nothing wrong with him.

380
00:25:49,055 --> 00:25:49,639
Goodbye.

381
00:25:50,012 --> 00:25:52,349
Where's all his
paintings, then?

382
00:25:52,787 --> 00:25:54,028
What are you
doing here?

383
00:25:54,029 --> 00:25:56,641
Would you please ask this man
to leave, Detective,

384
00:25:56,642 --> 00:25:58,042
and not come back again?

385
00:25:58,043 --> 00:26:00,141
Get out,
like the lady says.

386
00:26:09,454 --> 00:26:11,587
I warned you, didn't I?
Keep out of this.

387
00:26:11,588 --> 00:26:13,103
Was she his mistress?

388
00:26:13,660 --> 00:26:15,984
He was doing all right
for an old man.

389
00:26:15,985 --> 00:26:17,832
Maybe I should
take up painting.

390
00:26:17,833 --> 00:26:18,788
I'm giving her
24-hour protection

391
00:26:18,789 --> 00:26:19,937
for the next
couple of days.

392
00:26:19,938 --> 00:26:21,274
I'll tell my men
to arrest you

393
00:26:21,275 --> 00:26:22,932
if you show up here
again, all right?

394
00:26:22,933 --> 00:26:25,801
You never offered me
24-hour protection.

395
00:26:26,819 --> 00:26:28,794
Oh, come on, Frank.
It's obvious.

396
00:26:28,795 --> 00:26:30,132
It's got to be
Selina, the wife.

397
00:26:30,133 --> 00:26:31,474
She gets dumped
for a younger woman,

398
00:26:31,475 --> 00:26:32,427
thrown out of her home.

399
00:26:32,428 --> 00:26:33,320
She feels bitter.

400
00:26:33,321 --> 00:26:34,628
She doesn't want Stasio

401
00:26:34,629 --> 00:26:35,709
to go through with
divorcing her,

402
00:26:35,710 --> 00:26:36,666
so she kills him.

403
00:26:36,667 --> 00:26:37,431
Absolutely.

404
00:26:38,039 --> 00:26:39,501
There's only one drawback--
she didn't do it.

405
00:26:39,502 --> 00:26:40,651
How do you know?

406
00:26:40,652 --> 00:26:42,308
She was at a party
in London, all night,

407
00:26:42,309 --> 00:26:43,263
at least 20 witnesses.

408
00:26:43,264 --> 00:26:44,378
She didn't do it.

409
00:26:44,379 --> 00:26:45,844
And what about Angeline,
where was she?

410
00:26:45,845 --> 00:26:48,292
Come on, Frank,
I know you asked.

411
00:26:48,490 --> 00:26:50,115
I didn't have time to.

412
00:26:50,116 --> 00:26:53,214
She says she was
with the family solicitor.

413
00:26:53,684 --> 00:26:54,558
At midnight?

414
00:27:02,099 --> 00:27:03,271
[SEAGULLS CAWING]

415
00:27:06,784 --> 00:27:08,058
I don't
want you with me.

416
00:27:08,059 --> 00:27:09,110
Come on, Frank.

417
00:27:09,111 --> 00:27:10,863
Ton, don't make me have
an argument about it.

418
00:27:10,864 --> 00:27:12,775
Would it be all right
if I take the car?

419
00:27:12,776 --> 00:27:14,511
No, it ain't all right.

420
00:27:17,268 --> 00:27:17,780
Go on.

421
00:27:19,593 --> 00:27:21,889
I understand
you represented Stasio,

422
00:27:21,890 --> 00:27:22,700
Mr. Roscoe.

423
00:27:22,844 --> 00:27:24,087
Yes, that's correct.

424
00:27:24,088 --> 00:27:25,490
Why did you pick Tony's--

425
00:27:25,491 --> 00:27:28,405
Mr. Aaron's agency
to fake the adultery?

426
00:27:28,482 --> 00:27:29,441
Look, I'm not saying--

427
00:27:29,442 --> 00:27:30,397
It's all right.

428
00:27:30,398 --> 00:27:32,339
I'm not interested
in any of that.

429
00:27:32,340 --> 00:27:33,382
Why Mr. Aaron?

430
00:27:33,807 --> 00:27:35,080
Well, he'd, uh...

431
00:27:35,400 --> 00:27:38,169
done some work for me
a couple of times before...

432
00:27:38,170 --> 00:27:39,937
matrimonial, similar work.

433
00:27:40,624 --> 00:27:42,252
I didn't really know him.

434
00:27:42,253 --> 00:27:42,764
I see.

435
00:27:43,622 --> 00:27:46,069
What was Stasio like
as a client?

436
00:27:46,206 --> 00:27:47,256
Very difficult.

437
00:27:47,797 --> 00:27:49,325
He was forever
changing his mind.

438
00:27:49,326 --> 00:27:50,600
But he paid well.

439
00:27:52,099 --> 00:27:53,210
Is that a question?

440
00:27:53,211 --> 00:27:54,298
Why did you
meet Angeline

441
00:27:54,299 --> 00:27:55,667
the night
that he was murdered?

442
00:27:55,668 --> 00:27:57,063
That is a question.

443
00:27:57,519 --> 00:28:00,002
Mr. Stasio had instructed me
to invite her here

444
00:28:00,003 --> 00:28:02,288
to explain about the...
adultery

445
00:28:02,426 --> 00:28:04,110
when it was already
too late to stop it.

446
00:28:04,111 --> 00:28:05,325
She didn't know?

447
00:28:06,121 --> 00:28:07,077
Why didn't he tell her?

448
00:28:07,078 --> 00:28:08,669
You'd have to ask her.

449
00:28:08,670 --> 00:28:10,477
What time
did she leave?

450
00:28:10,552 --> 00:28:12,234
Very late. About 10:00.

451
00:28:12,334 --> 00:28:13,642
What did you do then?

452
00:28:13,643 --> 00:28:14,566
I went home.

453
00:30:04,542 --> 00:30:05,293
Mr. Aaron?

454
00:30:07,283 --> 00:30:08,035
Mr. Aaron!

455
00:30:14,294 --> 00:30:16,587
It's your own fault. I told you
not to come back here.

456
00:30:16,588 --> 00:30:17,391
I'm sorry.

457
00:30:19,773 --> 00:30:21,398
I didn't mean
to frighten you.

458
00:30:21,399 --> 00:30:23,215
You didn't frighten me.
I frightened you.

459
00:30:23,216 --> 00:30:25,063
It's a bit late
to be making pastry, isn't it?

460
00:30:25,064 --> 00:30:26,561
I think
you'll be fine.

461
00:30:26,562 --> 00:30:27,896
You can leave now.

462
00:30:30,704 --> 00:30:32,380
I don't want to leave.

463
00:30:33,765 --> 00:30:34,918
If I blow this,

464
00:30:35,200 --> 00:30:37,716
the two cops out front
will come running in here.

465
00:30:37,717 --> 00:30:39,852
I think
you should give that to me.

466
00:30:39,853 --> 00:30:44,164
I seem to be in more danger
of sudden violence than you do.

467
00:30:46,132 --> 00:30:47,365
[THUNDER CLAPPING]

468
00:31:18,477 --> 00:31:19,390
Is this you?

469
00:31:20,589 --> 00:31:22,098
It has
the curious effect

470
00:31:22,099 --> 00:31:24,874
of making strangers
think they know me.

471
00:31:28,590 --> 00:31:30,432
Where did you meet Stasio?

472
00:31:30,761 --> 00:31:32,493
At an exhibition
in Miami.

473
00:31:32,494 --> 00:31:33,658
I admired
his paintings.

474
00:31:33,659 --> 00:31:35,454
He asked me
to model for him.

475
00:31:35,455 --> 00:31:36,715
And here you are.

476
00:31:37,721 --> 00:31:38,793
I was an art student.

477
00:31:38,794 --> 00:31:39,958
I decided to
give up painting

478
00:31:39,959 --> 00:31:41,282
when I saw
what he could do

479
00:31:41,283 --> 00:31:42,660
with his eyes shut.

480
00:31:44,087 --> 00:31:45,944
An artist's work leaps in value
after his death,

481
00:31:45,945 --> 00:31:47,144
isn't that true?

482
00:31:47,487 --> 00:31:47,998
Always.

483
00:31:49,691 --> 00:31:52,020
You must be sitting
on a gold mine.

484
00:31:52,021 --> 00:31:53,881
Well, do you think
I killed him

485
00:31:53,882 --> 00:31:54,911
to make money?

486
00:31:56,464 --> 00:31:58,596
I was just
thinking out loud.

487
00:31:59,958 --> 00:32:02,037
I could take this painting
to any gallery in the world

488
00:32:02,038 --> 00:32:04,807
and get $20,000 for it,
probably more.

489
00:32:14,575 --> 00:32:17,269
If you take it out,
you can keep it.

490
00:32:22,101 --> 00:32:24,231
What are you
trying to prove?

491
00:32:24,652 --> 00:32:26,199
It's a serious offer.

492
00:32:39,520 --> 00:32:41,007
I wanted to show you

493
00:32:41,254 --> 00:32:43,047
you care more about money
than I do.

494
00:32:43,048 --> 00:32:43,851
Yeah, well,

495
00:32:44,184 --> 00:32:47,167
you've got more of it
to not care about.

496
00:32:51,618 --> 00:32:52,529
It's signed.

497
00:32:52,686 --> 00:32:53,082
Yeah?

498
00:32:54,640 --> 00:32:56,780
All these paintings are signed.

499
00:32:56,811 --> 00:32:59,836
I thought famous painters
didn't sign their work

500
00:32:59,837 --> 00:33:00,909
until it was sold,

501
00:33:00,910 --> 00:33:02,417
to stop people
stealing them.

502
00:33:02,418 --> 00:33:04,333
People
can steal paintings.

503
00:33:04,437 --> 00:33:06,201
People can forge signatures,

504
00:33:06,202 --> 00:33:08,926
so Stasio did something
really clever--

505
00:33:10,293 --> 00:33:13,057
he put his thumb print
after his name.

506
00:33:14,294 --> 00:33:16,876
Only the ones on the wall
have his thumb print on them.

507
00:33:16,877 --> 00:33:18,496
The rest are worthless.

508
00:33:19,050 --> 00:33:20,318
Pretty smart, huh?

509
00:33:23,018 --> 00:33:24,346
Yeah, pretty smart.

510
00:33:33,602 --> 00:33:35,302
Now you've had the tour.

511
00:33:35,303 --> 00:33:37,194
You hated him, didn't you?

512
00:33:38,264 --> 00:33:39,752
Why do you say that?

513
00:33:41,979 --> 00:33:43,585
He was an amazing man.

514
00:33:44,092 --> 00:33:47,027
He was the most powerful man
I ever met,

515
00:33:47,433 --> 00:33:49,333
but he was... so obsessive,

516
00:33:51,177 --> 00:33:53,606
and he became...
obsessed with me.

517
00:33:56,059 --> 00:33:57,495
He threw Selina out.

518
00:33:57,508 --> 00:33:59,872
He said he'd divorce her
and marry me,

519
00:33:59,873 --> 00:34:02,172
even though I kept telling him
I was going back to America.

520
00:34:02,173 --> 00:34:03,496
I didn't mean to stay with him.

521
00:34:03,497 --> 00:34:05,865
Things just...
got out of hand...

522
00:34:08,437 --> 00:34:10,580
and then, he wouldn't let me go.

523
00:34:10,581 --> 00:34:12,475
He said
he'd kill himself

524
00:34:12,659 --> 00:34:13,452
if I left.

525
00:34:15,054 --> 00:34:16,956
Maybe that's what happened.

526
00:34:17,919 --> 00:34:21,388
Maybe he shot your wife
and then... shot himself.

527
00:34:21,417 --> 00:34:22,219
Yeah, sure,

528
00:34:23,117 --> 00:34:25,872
and then what did he do
with the gun?

529
00:34:48,060 --> 00:34:48,401
Son?

530
00:34:49,480 --> 00:34:51,023
What am I supposed
to be looking at?

531
00:34:51,024 --> 00:34:52,808
You weren't there, Frank.

532
00:34:53,764 --> 00:34:54,808
Look carefully.

533
00:34:59,466 --> 00:35:01,906
Tony had this
shooting competition.

534
00:35:11,937 --> 00:35:12,572
Souvenir?

535
00:35:13,671 --> 00:35:15,341
A souvenir, from the war.

536
00:35:15,342 --> 00:35:16,996
Why did you lie to me?

537
00:35:17,733 --> 00:35:19,964
for it, and I'm in enough shit

538
00:35:20,189 --> 00:35:23,521
as it is, all right?
No, it is not all right.

539
00:35:24,286 --> 00:35:24,853
Get it.

540
00:35:28,632 --> 00:35:30,049
I'd forgotten all about it.

541
00:35:30,050 --> 00:35:31,706
Don't make a big deal.

542
00:35:40,035 --> 00:35:40,945
It was here.

543
00:35:43,278 --> 00:35:44,825
I swear
it was here.

544
00:35:55,942 --> 00:35:56,734
It's gone.

545
00:35:56,952 --> 00:35:58,661
I know it was in there.

546
00:36:00,572 --> 00:36:01,771
It's been taken.

547
00:36:02,681 --> 00:36:04,099
Hazel was playing with it
last week.

548
00:36:04,100 --> 00:36:05,610
She must have put it somewhere.

549
00:36:05,611 --> 00:36:08,662
This is the gun
you'd forgotten all about?

550
00:36:13,393 --> 00:36:14,253
[LOW VOICES]

551
00:36:19,975 --> 00:36:20,896
Good morning!

552
00:36:20,918 --> 00:36:22,292
What are you doing?

553
00:36:23,283 --> 00:36:24,195
May I ask...

554
00:36:25,046 --> 00:36:26,966
where did you go
when you left the solicitor's

555
00:36:26,967 --> 00:36:28,101
on the night of the murder?

556
00:36:28,102 --> 00:36:29,944
Home.
What are you doing?

557
00:36:30,621 --> 00:36:31,602
Straight home?

558
00:36:31,849 --> 00:36:33,361
I may have driven around
for a while,

559
00:36:33,362 --> 00:36:34,651
I was pretty upset.

560
00:36:34,652 --> 00:36:35,972
You'll have to do
better than that.

561
00:36:35,973 --> 00:36:37,233
I had few drinks.

562
00:36:37,738 --> 00:36:39,185
I don't remember
exactly where I went.

563
00:36:39,186 --> 00:36:40,197
What are you looking for?

564
00:36:40,198 --> 00:36:41,141
Lots of things.

565
00:36:41,142 --> 00:36:41,885
Like what?

566
00:36:42,114 --> 00:36:44,248
Now, this is a search warrant.

567
00:36:44,320 --> 00:36:45,006
I wonder,

568
00:36:45,266 --> 00:36:46,297
would you mind

569
00:36:46,465 --> 00:36:49,052
if we took a look
around the villa?

570
00:36:51,693 --> 00:36:52,557
[DOOR BANGS]

571
00:36:54,594 --> 00:36:56,060
Did you tell
the police something

572
00:36:56,061 --> 00:36:57,403
to make them tear my car apart?

573
00:36:57,404 --> 00:36:57,686
No.

574
00:36:58,869 --> 00:36:59,152
No?

575
00:36:59,992 --> 00:37:00,270
No.

576
00:37:08,936 --> 00:37:09,919
You see, I...

577
00:37:11,009 --> 00:37:13,509
I did go to the hotel
that night.

578
00:37:14,779 --> 00:37:17,139
Mr. Roscoe told me
what Carlo was going to do,

579
00:37:17,140 --> 00:37:19,535
and I wanted
to try and stop him.

580
00:37:19,536 --> 00:37:22,161
I--
I wasn't going to marry him....

581
00:37:23,306 --> 00:37:25,920
But I knew
he'd fly into a rage...

582
00:37:26,466 --> 00:37:28,319
so I just sat in my car.

583
00:37:32,344 --> 00:37:34,165
You sat in your car?
You didn't go inside?

584
00:37:34,166 --> 00:37:38,147
I should have told the police,
but I was so frightened.

585
00:37:39,562 --> 00:37:42,064
I mean, it looks bad,
doesn't it?

586
00:37:50,967 --> 00:37:52,559
I think his wife killed him.

587
00:37:52,560 --> 00:37:54,191
She was 50 miles away.

588
00:37:57,351 --> 00:37:57,634
Oh.

589
00:38:00,387 --> 00:38:03,190
Well, maybe she paid someone
to do it.

590
00:38:03,583 --> 00:38:04,827
Go and talk to her.

591
00:38:04,828 --> 00:38:07,415
Hey, listen, I'm doing
my investigations, not yours.

592
00:38:07,416 --> 00:38:08,450
I'll pay you.

593
00:38:09,298 --> 00:38:10,672
To find my wife's killer?

594
00:38:10,673 --> 00:38:12,842
What kind of person
do you think I am?

595
00:38:12,843 --> 00:38:13,779
Hello, girls.

596
00:38:15,877 --> 00:38:17,576
Someone who needs money.

597
00:38:22,231 --> 00:38:24,531
You could use it to move
into a nicer neighborhood.

598
00:38:24,532 --> 00:38:26,462
My mother was a prostitute.

599
00:38:26,478 --> 00:38:27,875
I like living here.

600
00:38:30,638 --> 00:38:30,916
Oh.

601
00:38:33,093 --> 00:38:33,724
Yes. Oh.

602
00:38:37,467 --> 00:38:39,274
Did you know your father?

603
00:38:42,131 --> 00:38:44,466
Oh, yes.
I knew all my fathers.

604
00:38:48,357 --> 00:38:50,182
What time did
your husband get home

605
00:38:50,183 --> 00:38:51,870
on the night
of the murder?

606
00:38:51,871 --> 00:38:53,407
Well, you don't think
my husband was involved?

607
00:38:53,408 --> 00:38:54,984
Good gracious, no. No.

608
00:38:55,321 --> 00:38:56,791
I just want to clarify
in my mind

609
00:38:56,792 --> 00:38:58,428
the sequence of events.

610
00:38:59,280 --> 00:39:00,337
About midnight.

611
00:39:01,291 --> 00:39:03,462
He works very
late these days.

612
00:39:03,463 --> 00:39:06,910
I was just falling asleep
when I heard the car.

613
00:39:16,879 --> 00:39:18,639
What are you doing
harassing my wife?

614
00:39:18,640 --> 00:39:19,442
I'm sorry?

615
00:39:19,593 --> 00:39:20,682
If you have any questions,

616
00:39:20,684 --> 00:39:22,246
you come to the office
and ask them.

617
00:39:22,247 --> 00:39:23,203
I have one question.

618
00:39:23,204 --> 00:39:24,892
If you left the office
at 10:00,

619
00:39:24,893 --> 00:39:28,088
why did it take you two hours
to drive three miles home?

620
00:39:28,089 --> 00:39:30,549
Did you go to the hotel
with Angeline?

621
00:39:30,550 --> 00:39:31,955
I don't have to talk to you.

622
00:39:31,956 --> 00:39:32,911
Oh, you do...

623
00:39:32,911 --> 00:39:34,080
sooner or later.

624
00:40:16,126 --> 00:40:17,179
I'm Inspector Vance.

625
00:40:17,180 --> 00:40:19,640
We met at
your husband's memorial.

626
00:40:19,641 --> 00:40:20,723
But I've already
been talking

627
00:40:20,724 --> 00:40:22,032
to Inspector Aaron.

628
00:40:22,033 --> 00:40:22,740
Inspector?

629
00:40:23,666 --> 00:40:26,091
I'm going to have
to sort him out.

630
00:40:26,092 --> 00:40:27,478
Can I have a word?

631
00:40:33,628 --> 00:40:35,378
He'd had affairs before.

632
00:40:35,609 --> 00:40:37,369
We had
an understanding.

633
00:40:37,652 --> 00:40:39,029
He swore that
they were nothing,

634
00:40:39,030 --> 00:40:41,005
and that he'd
never leave me.

635
00:40:41,006 --> 00:40:42,062
Until Angeline.

636
00:40:42,443 --> 00:40:45,601
When he came back
from Miami, he'd changed.

637
00:40:46,406 --> 00:40:48,034
He was completely
under her spell,

638
00:40:48,035 --> 00:40:49,216
did anything she said.

639
00:40:49,217 --> 00:40:51,197
She's a very
persuasive woman,

640
00:40:51,198 --> 00:40:52,071
very clever.

641
00:40:52,409 --> 00:40:54,770
Are you sure you're not just...
jealous?

642
00:40:54,771 --> 00:40:56,399
Of course I'm jealous.

643
00:40:57,613 --> 00:41:00,187
I've made myself ill
with jealousy.

644
00:41:05,247 --> 00:41:08,657
That was his first American
exhibition in Miami.

645
00:41:09,049 --> 00:41:11,059
I was an art dealer,
that's how we met.

646
00:41:11,060 --> 00:41:12,594
Of course,
I had to give that all up

647
00:41:12,595 --> 00:41:14,383
as soon as we were married.

648
00:41:14,384 --> 00:41:16,427
No wife of his
was allowed to work.

649
00:41:16,428 --> 00:41:18,218
I don't care he's dead.

650
00:41:19,208 --> 00:41:21,314
I could lie,
but I don't care.

651
00:41:21,315 --> 00:41:23,710
I stopped loving him
long before he...

652
00:41:23,711 --> 00:41:24,697
threw me out.

653
00:41:25,530 --> 00:41:28,309
Stop going around saying
you're a policeman.

654
00:41:28,310 --> 00:41:30,640
In fact, stop going
around all together.

655
00:41:30,641 --> 00:41:32,013
You're making me
look like an idiot,

656
00:41:32,014 --> 00:41:33,931
arriving five minutes
after you all the time.

657
00:41:33,932 --> 00:41:36,101
Frank, I can't help it
if I'm ahead of the game.

658
00:41:36,102 --> 00:41:37,124
Do you think
she's involved?

659
00:41:37,125 --> 00:41:37,404
No.

660
00:41:38,083 --> 00:41:39,679
She's a very
bitter woman

661
00:41:39,680 --> 00:41:41,115
who'd love
to get her hands

662
00:41:41,116 --> 00:41:42,075
back into paintings,

663
00:41:42,076 --> 00:41:43,030
but she's innocent.

664
00:41:43,031 --> 00:41:44,079
It's Angeline.

665
00:41:44,313 --> 00:41:46,887
Car was spotless,
so was the villa.

666
00:41:47,314 --> 00:41:48,558
Frank, she's ice cool.

667
00:41:48,559 --> 00:41:50,667
Like, today she come in here
and tried to hire me

668
00:41:50,668 --> 00:41:52,167
to investigate the murders
that she committed.

669
00:41:52,168 --> 00:41:54,731
I don't want you
seeing her again.

670
00:41:55,680 --> 00:41:57,597
I know why they cut
his thumb off, you know.

671
00:41:57,599 --> 00:41:58,903
It was to
authenticate the--

672
00:41:58,904 --> 00:42:00,855
Paintings, yeah.
Well done, Detective.

673
00:42:00,856 --> 00:42:03,248
You're not
the only one working.

674
00:42:04,083 --> 00:42:04,958
Frank, look,

675
00:42:05,519 --> 00:42:06,954
Stasio had homes
in America, in Italy.

676
00:42:06,955 --> 00:42:08,676
Supposing there's
hundreds of paintings

677
00:42:08,677 --> 00:42:09,986
lying all over the world,

678
00:42:09,987 --> 00:42:12,257
all worthless without
the thumbprint.

679
00:42:12,258 --> 00:42:13,727
Oh, Frank, she did it.

680
00:42:13,728 --> 00:42:14,529
I know it.

681
00:42:19,605 --> 00:42:21,392
Everyone thinks
I murdered them,

682
00:42:21,393 --> 00:42:22,256
don't they?

683
00:42:23,020 --> 00:42:23,305
No.

684
00:42:25,447 --> 00:42:26,980
I saw a man
on the fire escape

685
00:42:26,981 --> 00:42:28,964
that night when
I was in my car.

686
00:42:28,965 --> 00:42:29,656
Oh, yeah?

687
00:42:30,463 --> 00:42:31,994
What did he look like?

688
00:42:31,995 --> 00:42:34,619
It was dark.
I couldn't really see.

689
00:42:35,030 --> 00:42:36,370
Well, what height
was he?

690
00:42:36,371 --> 00:42:38,233
And don't say
my height.

691
00:42:38,769 --> 00:42:39,815
Couldn't tell.

692
00:42:40,139 --> 00:42:41,416
Did you tell
the police?

693
00:42:41,417 --> 00:42:43,799
Mm. They'll think
I made it up.

694
00:42:45,694 --> 00:42:47,628
Were you happy
with Hazel?

695
00:42:48,861 --> 00:42:49,896
I don't know.

696
00:42:49,948 --> 00:42:51,957
I'm not an expert
in marriages.

697
00:42:51,958 --> 00:42:53,107
When you were with her,

698
00:42:53,108 --> 00:42:54,513
did you want to be
with other people?

699
00:42:54,514 --> 00:42:56,113
Oh, yes.
All the time.

700
00:42:56,114 --> 00:42:57,862
I love women.
I lose my head.

701
00:42:57,863 --> 00:42:59,366
Do you think people
know what they're doing,

702
00:42:59,367 --> 00:43:00,771
or do you think we're...

703
00:43:00,772 --> 00:43:03,285
driven by things
we can't control.

704
00:43:04,061 --> 00:43:06,040
People are capable
of anything.

705
00:43:06,041 --> 00:43:07,961
A boat goes down in
the middle of the ocean,

706
00:43:07,962 --> 00:43:09,297
and it's not
the women and children

707
00:43:09,298 --> 00:43:10,640
who get out first,

708
00:43:10,771 --> 00:43:11,921
it's the people
that are ready

709
00:43:11,922 --> 00:43:13,551
to step on the others.

710
00:43:13,834 --> 00:43:15,225
You're so like me.

711
00:43:15,721 --> 00:43:16,171
Am I?

712
00:43:17,510 --> 00:43:19,553
You don't really
like yourself, do you?

713
00:43:19,554 --> 00:43:22,649
Things'd be different
if I was in America.

714
00:43:23,640 --> 00:43:25,170
I'd be
a different person,

715
00:43:25,171 --> 00:43:26,097
a new start.

716
00:43:30,826 --> 00:43:32,235
I understand Selina.

717
00:43:32,586 --> 00:43:35,236
She's more like me
than I care to admit.

718
00:43:35,237 --> 00:43:38,460
Nobody likes being used
and then thrown away.

719
00:43:38,622 --> 00:43:40,832
So why did you
stay with him?

720
00:43:41,240 --> 00:43:43,507
Because I need people
to tell me that they love me,

721
00:43:43,508 --> 00:43:44,722
and when they do,

722
00:43:44,723 --> 00:43:47,371
I get frightened
and want to run away.

723
00:43:47,372 --> 00:43:49,383
You're not answering
my question.

724
00:43:49,384 --> 00:43:50,563
If he was so terrible,
why did--

725
00:43:50,564 --> 00:43:51,561
[BRANCH SNAPS]

726
00:43:52,803 --> 00:43:54,462
There's somebody
out there.

727
00:43:54,463 --> 00:43:56,554
Let's go back
to the house.

728
00:43:56,857 --> 00:43:57,965
Are you joking?

729
00:44:20,460 --> 00:44:22,512
Is everything else locked up?

730
00:44:26,945 --> 00:44:29,622
I feel safe
as long as you're here.

731
00:44:32,121 --> 00:44:34,040
Well... I can't stay here.

732
00:44:34,866 --> 00:44:37,723
You don't have anywhere
to go, do you?

733
00:44:41,829 --> 00:44:44,341
Look...
I just can't get involved.

734
00:44:58,821 --> 00:45:00,930
Why don't you go down
to the cellar and...

735
00:45:00,931 --> 00:45:01,973
choose a wine?

736
00:45:03,773 --> 00:45:04,575
It's late.

737
00:45:04,952 --> 00:45:06,882
I know nothing
about wine.

738
00:45:08,530 --> 00:45:11,517
Then choose a bottle
with a pretty label.

739
00:45:28,620 --> 00:45:29,725
Oh, very funny.

740
00:45:31,556 --> 00:45:32,201
Angeline?

741
00:45:37,719 --> 00:45:38,485
Angeline...

742
00:46:03,305 --> 00:46:07,515
I don't think you're supposed
to serve Bordeaux like that.

743
00:46:26,622 --> 00:46:27,777
I'm going home.

744
00:46:33,042 --> 00:46:33,905
Go on then.

745
00:46:44,956 --> 00:46:46,102
Why did you
stay with him?

746
00:46:46,103 --> 00:46:46,505
What?

747
00:46:47,093 --> 00:46:47,616
Stasio,

748
00:46:48,117 --> 00:46:49,171
If he was so awful,

749
00:46:49,172 --> 00:46:51,441
why did you
stay with him, hm?

750
00:46:51,502 --> 00:46:52,684
I can't believe you,

751
00:46:52,685 --> 00:46:55,786
cross-examining me
while we're making love.

752
00:47:00,445 --> 00:47:02,303
You know
who I am, Tony?

753
00:47:04,087 --> 00:47:04,781
Ah... Ah.

754
00:47:05,491 --> 00:47:06,013
Nobody.

755
00:47:08,590 --> 00:47:11,281
But I've met Picasso,
Brock, Matisse,

756
00:47:12,418 --> 00:47:15,552
I've been to Mexico,
Paris, the South Seas,

757
00:47:15,553 --> 00:47:17,755
and places
people only dream about.

758
00:47:17,755 --> 00:47:19,701
When I die,
I'll still exist.

759
00:47:19,702 --> 00:47:20,664
People will stare at me

760
00:47:20,665 --> 00:47:22,005
in galleries
all over the world.

761
00:47:22,006 --> 00:47:23,440
We're nothing,
you and me.

762
00:47:23,441 --> 00:47:24,908
We'll only
get out of the gutter

763
00:47:24,909 --> 00:47:26,282
on someone else's back.

764
00:47:26,283 --> 00:47:28,044
Everybody can be special.

765
00:47:30,054 --> 00:47:33,188
You and me, we burn
to be what we're not.

766
00:47:33,978 --> 00:47:35,608
We have to be special,

767
00:47:35,673 --> 00:47:37,885
and we'll do
anything for it.

768
00:47:39,058 --> 00:47:41,293
Wouldn't you
do anything for it?

769
00:47:41,294 --> 00:47:42,280
Oh, yes. Yes.

770
00:48:10,007 --> 00:48:12,629
Frank, wait. Wait.
I can't do this.

771
00:48:22,688 --> 00:48:24,022
You be the killer.

772
00:48:40,698 --> 00:48:41,222
Okay...

773
00:48:43,253 --> 00:48:43,838
Right...

774
00:48:45,584 --> 00:48:48,038
Okay, I come in
through the door.

775
00:48:53,858 --> 00:48:56,021
I kill them both,
shoot them.

776
00:49:01,972 --> 00:49:04,302
I, uh, cut off his thumb here...

777
00:49:09,703 --> 00:49:10,516
Then leave.

778
00:49:10,658 --> 00:49:10,940
No.

779
00:49:12,380 --> 00:49:14,907
Why didn't they try
and get up out of bed?

780
00:49:14,908 --> 00:49:15,865
Why'd they just sit there?

781
00:49:15,866 --> 00:49:18,598
Why'd they let you
pick up a pillow?

782
00:49:18,644 --> 00:49:19,461
Okay, okay.

783
00:49:19,698 --> 00:49:21,455
They're not frightened...

784
00:49:21,838 --> 00:49:22,795
because they know me.

785
00:49:22,796 --> 00:49:23,779
That's right.

786
00:49:24,011 --> 00:49:25,255
One of them knows me.

787
00:49:25,256 --> 00:49:27,840
And the killer never came in
through that door.

788
00:49:27,841 --> 00:49:30,045
Look at the direction
of the blood on the wall.

789
00:49:30,046 --> 00:49:31,865
They're both turned
towards the bathroom.

790
00:49:31,866 --> 00:49:33,552
You're being very slow.

791
00:49:42,281 --> 00:49:44,150
Bathroom's
got a balcony.

792
00:49:44,227 --> 00:49:45,758
A sash with
a sliding lock.

793
00:49:45,759 --> 00:49:48,684
The easiest window
in the world to open.

794
00:49:51,702 --> 00:49:52,877
[SEAGULLS CAWING]

795
00:50:00,054 --> 00:50:01,799
There's
no fire escape.

796
00:50:02,424 --> 00:50:03,567
I wouldn't want
to chance this

797
00:50:03,568 --> 00:50:04,522
as an escape route,

798
00:50:04,523 --> 00:50:05,475
especially at night.

799
00:50:05,476 --> 00:50:06,811
Why are you assuming

800
00:50:06,812 --> 00:50:09,021
that the killer
left the hotel

801
00:50:09,102 --> 00:50:10,382
after the murders?

802
00:50:19,401 --> 00:50:20,826
He went over the roof.

803
00:50:21,827 --> 00:50:22,229
Shit.

804
00:50:41,955 --> 00:50:43,633
This window
leads to the kitchen.

805
00:50:43,634 --> 00:50:45,700
It's closed in the evenings
in winter.

806
00:50:45,701 --> 00:50:47,322
From here,
no one can see you

807
00:50:47,323 --> 00:50:49,326
if you walk back downstairs
into the lobby.

808
00:50:49,327 --> 00:50:50,596
It's good, Frank.

809
00:50:50,821 --> 00:50:52,729
There's only one thing
that worries me about this--

810
00:50:52,730 --> 00:50:53,938
where's the gun?

811
00:50:56,734 --> 00:50:58,483
Everyone in the hotel
was searched,

812
00:50:58,484 --> 00:50:59,719
checked the rooms,

813
00:50:59,720 --> 00:51:01,419
rubbish tips, everything,

814
00:51:01,469 --> 00:51:02,041
no gun.

815
00:51:04,206 --> 00:51:05,188
Walk back, will you?

816
00:51:05,189 --> 00:51:06,640
Go through it again.

817
00:51:09,003 --> 00:51:11,205
What did they do with the gun?

818
00:51:17,776 --> 00:51:18,732
Wait a minute!

819
00:51:18,733 --> 00:51:20,179
Where do those lead?

820
00:51:24,356 --> 00:51:27,091
Yeah, heat's the water
for the whole hotel.

821
00:51:27,092 --> 00:51:28,233
I stoke it up at night,

822
00:51:28,234 --> 00:51:29,793
and then again
first thing in the morning.

823
00:51:29,794 --> 00:51:31,351
How often is it
turned off?

824
00:51:31,352 --> 00:51:34,143
Never. It's designed
so that the ashes

825
00:51:34,243 --> 00:51:36,395
drop through
to a tray below.

826
00:51:40,506 --> 00:51:42,366
What are you
looking for?

827
00:51:45,846 --> 00:51:47,562
There's something
at the back there,

828
00:51:47,563 --> 00:51:48,196
you see?

829
00:51:48,579 --> 00:51:50,908
You reckon
you could reach that?

830
00:52:10,960 --> 00:52:12,005
What make
was your gun?

831
00:52:12,005 --> 00:52:12,818
Oh, Frank--

832
00:52:12,963 --> 00:52:14,702
What make
was your gun?

833
00:52:16,392 --> 00:52:16,976
Beretta.

834
00:52:17,350 --> 00:52:18,969
I have to
arrest you.

835
00:52:19,190 --> 00:52:19,991
I have to.

836
00:52:20,428 --> 00:52:23,169
Somebody's setting me up,
here, Frank.

837
00:52:23,931 --> 00:52:25,076
Look, I didn't
tell you this,

838
00:52:25,077 --> 00:52:26,597
but a few days ago,
I came back,

839
00:52:26,598 --> 00:52:28,120
and the office door
had been forced open.

840
00:52:28,121 --> 00:52:29,078
Now, I didn't
see anything--

841
00:52:29,079 --> 00:52:30,061
Don't even start.

842
00:52:30,062 --> 00:52:31,081
But it's true.

843
00:52:31,082 --> 00:52:32,095
If I give this
to Waterston,

844
00:52:32,096 --> 00:52:33,246
This is enough
to convict you.

845
00:52:33,247 --> 00:52:34,672
It's Angeline,
she did it.

846
00:52:34,673 --> 00:52:36,008
She was outside
the hotel that night.

847
00:52:36,009 --> 00:52:37,119
I know she did it.

848
00:52:37,120 --> 00:52:38,011
Why, what was
her motive?

849
00:52:38,012 --> 00:52:39,154
Frank,
she hated him--

850
00:52:39,155 --> 00:52:40,615
Tony, I am holding
your fucking gun.

851
00:52:40,616 --> 00:52:42,908
Look, you've got to keep this
to yourself for a few days.

852
00:52:42,909 --> 00:52:44,620
No, no.
Two days. We can nail her.

853
00:52:44,621 --> 00:52:45,316
24 hours.

854
00:52:45,578 --> 00:52:46,564
What if anyone
finds out

855
00:52:46,565 --> 00:52:47,449
I'm holding
back evidence?

856
00:52:47,450 --> 00:52:48,533
Frank, what's more
important to you,

857
00:52:48,534 --> 00:52:49,805
our old friendship
or police procedure?

858
00:52:49,806 --> 00:52:51,396
Don't you useour friendship--
Why not? Why not?

859
00:52:51,397 --> 00:52:53,368
What else
have I got left?

860
00:52:53,747 --> 00:52:55,651
You were the only one
who stuck by me, Frank,

861
00:52:55,654 --> 00:52:56,633
the only one.

862
00:52:58,514 --> 00:52:59,725
Stick by me now.

863
00:53:20,862 --> 00:53:23,291
I could get
in a lot of trouble.

864
00:53:26,966 --> 00:53:28,583
No details
about the will

865
00:53:28,585 --> 00:53:30,628
have yet
been made public...

866
00:53:49,155 --> 00:53:52,663
Mrs. Stasio, well,
you know each other, obviously.

867
00:53:54,235 --> 00:53:55,337
Shall we begin?

868
00:53:57,327 --> 00:53:59,291
The will is a document
of considerable length,

869
00:53:59,292 --> 00:54:00,865
and the deceased names

870
00:54:01,012 --> 00:54:02,918
