of art foundations and libraries

871
00:54:02,919 --> 00:54:05,460
who are to receive
his diaries and sketch books

872
00:54:05,461 --> 00:54:06,732
and other effects,

873
00:54:06,733 --> 00:54:07,779
but I'll concentrate first

874
00:54:07,780 --> 00:54:09,113
on the main division
of the estate

875
00:54:09,114 --> 00:54:10,393
and the paintings,

876
00:54:11,339 --> 00:54:14,281
which is considerably
more straightforward.

877
00:54:14,927 --> 00:54:16,684
"To my dearest
Angeline,

878
00:54:18,051 --> 00:54:20,019
"I leave everything
I possess,

879
00:54:20,020 --> 00:54:22,459
to be disposed of
as she wishes."

880
00:54:25,774 --> 00:54:26,934
It's outrageous!

881
00:54:27,554 --> 00:54:28,353
That's it?

882
00:54:28,510 --> 00:54:29,138
But I...

883
00:54:30,826 --> 00:54:33,306
That's it?
She gets all the paintings?

884
00:54:33,307 --> 00:54:35,311
There is
no reference to you

885
00:54:35,312 --> 00:54:37,055
in the will,
Mrs. Stasio.

886
00:54:37,056 --> 00:54:40,478
But I was with him
when he wrote his will, I--

887
00:54:41,318 --> 00:54:42,885
When was this written?

888
00:54:43,768 --> 00:54:45,007
When was it written?

889
00:54:45,008 --> 00:54:46,695
December the 21st, 1959.

890
00:54:47,134 --> 00:54:48,346
The day he died.

891
00:54:49,074 --> 00:54:51,426
He changes his will
so that she gets everything,

892
00:54:51,427 --> 00:54:53,868
and that same day,
he's murdered.

893
00:54:55,495 --> 00:54:56,248
You bitch.

894
00:54:57,687 --> 00:54:58,987
You couldn't wait.

895
00:54:58,988 --> 00:55:00,675
As soon as
he'd signed everything,

896
00:55:00,676 --> 00:55:02,076
you got rid of him,
didn't you?

897
00:55:02,077 --> 00:55:04,339
I told you, Frank,
I told you.

898
00:55:04,682 --> 00:55:06,942
She got his name
on the paper-- bang.

899
00:55:06,943 --> 00:55:08,271
That will is
completely legal.

900
00:55:08,272 --> 00:55:09,480
She's going to walk away
with everything.

901
00:55:09,481 --> 00:55:10,434
There's something
about Roscoe

902
00:55:10,435 --> 00:55:11,386
I don't buy.

903
00:55:11,387 --> 00:55:12,340
Maybe they're
in it together.

904
00:55:12,341 --> 00:55:13,295
I'm going to tail him.

905
00:55:13,296 --> 00:55:13,695
What?

906
00:55:14,756 --> 00:55:16,349
Frank, what does she have
to do to convince you?

907
00:55:16,350 --> 00:55:18,095
Look, it's got nothing
to do with bloody Roscoe,

908
00:55:18,096 --> 00:55:19,907
it's Angeline, and I can
nail her, she trusts me.

909
00:55:19,908 --> 00:55:21,787
Don't you go up there again.
You leave her to me.

910
00:55:21,788 --> 00:55:25,377
Look, I'm just going to
talk to her, that's all.

911
00:55:47,531 --> 00:55:49,613
I just want
to talk to you.

912
00:57:07,589 --> 00:57:08,981
What are you doing?

913
00:57:10,073 --> 00:57:11,029
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

914
00:57:12,030 --> 00:57:12,982
You were looking
for something,

915
00:57:12,983 --> 00:57:13,905
weren't you?

916
00:57:13,934 --> 00:57:14,889
You think
I murdered them?

917
00:57:14,890 --> 00:57:15,171
No.

918
00:57:15,846 --> 00:57:16,368
Get out of here.
Go on, get out.

919
00:57:16,369 --> 00:57:17,899
Look, I'm sorry.
I had to be sure.

920
00:57:17,900 --> 00:57:19,141
Stay away from me.

921
00:57:19,141 --> 00:57:20,285
Angeline,
I can't stay away from you.

922
00:57:20,286 --> 00:57:21,781
Everyone thinks
I murdered him to get his money.

923
00:57:21,782 --> 00:57:22,768
I don't care
about the money,

924
00:57:22,769 --> 00:57:23,817
and I don't want
the paintings.

925
00:57:23,818 --> 00:57:24,898
Look, I know
you didn't do it.

926
00:57:24,899 --> 00:57:26,107
You don't know.
I do.

927
00:57:26,108 --> 00:57:27,603
How can you know?
How can you say that

928
00:57:27,604 --> 00:57:28,843
after I find you searching
through everything?

929
00:57:28,844 --> 00:57:29,801
How can I trust you?

930
00:57:29,802 --> 00:57:31,486
Because we have
to trust each other.

931
00:57:31,487 --> 00:57:33,577
We have to trust
each other.

932
00:57:34,701 --> 00:57:35,564
We have to.

933
00:57:38,010 --> 00:57:38,991
We have to...

934
00:57:41,257 --> 00:57:42,237
Come with me.

935
00:57:42,275 --> 00:57:44,427
I want to show
you somewhere.

936
00:57:58,186 --> 00:57:59,881
[GARAGE DOOR BANGS OPEN]

937
00:58:22,591 --> 00:58:23,640
[WOMEN TALKING]

938
00:58:44,750 --> 00:58:46,132
Can I have a word?

939
00:58:57,509 --> 00:58:59,011
Go away, we're busy.

940
00:59:01,966 --> 00:59:02,481
Police.

941
00:59:04,953 --> 00:59:05,525
Oh, no.

942
00:59:08,201 --> 00:59:09,697
Have I got things wrong.

943
00:59:09,698 --> 00:59:10,749
What's going on?

944
00:59:10,750 --> 00:59:14,074
I think you better wait
in the kitchen, sonny.

945
00:59:17,939 --> 00:59:19,960
You're in a lot of trouble.

946
00:59:20,769 --> 00:59:24,815
I'm sure I don't need to remind
you of the law, do I?

947
00:59:25,704 --> 00:59:26,627
Can I, uh...

948
00:59:27,997 --> 00:59:28,949
Can I get dressed?

949
00:59:28,950 --> 00:59:29,225
No.

950
00:59:32,606 --> 00:59:35,871
We had a bit of trouble
selling this place...

951
00:59:36,173 --> 00:59:38,172
and I kept the key
that Hazel gave me.

952
00:59:38,173 --> 00:59:39,920
I come here quite often.

953
00:59:47,723 --> 00:59:49,700
No, the lights
don't work.

954
00:59:50,394 --> 00:59:51,411
A club owner
lived here.

955
00:59:51,412 --> 00:59:53,337
He was planning
a robbery.

956
00:59:54,943 --> 00:59:56,281
We just had to
watch the place.

957
00:59:56,282 --> 00:59:57,735
It wasn't dangerous.

958
00:59:58,415 --> 01:00:00,992
Two other policemen
were watching his club.

959
01:00:00,993 --> 01:00:03,256
I got to know
his wife, Hazel.

960
01:00:03,791 --> 01:00:05,315
Kept coming in
to see her, every night.

961
01:00:05,316 --> 01:00:06,939
Frank warned
me to stop,

962
01:00:06,940 --> 01:00:08,095
but I wouldn't.

963
01:00:08,596 --> 01:00:10,278
I couldn't stop myself.

964
01:00:11,013 --> 01:00:12,096
Then one night,

965
01:00:12,097 --> 01:00:14,229
another policeman,
Colin, got...

966
01:00:14,229 --> 01:00:16,208
into trouble
because of me.

967
01:00:17,058 --> 01:00:18,330
I got him killed.

968
01:00:19,767 --> 01:00:21,355
Sometimes-- Sometimes,
I think of my life

969
01:00:21,356 --> 01:00:23,265
as the same bad thing
played over and over again--

970
01:00:23,266 --> 01:00:25,464
This isn't the same,
you're innocent.

971
01:00:25,465 --> 01:00:28,146
You have nothing
to be frightened of.

972
01:00:28,419 --> 01:00:31,854
But I'm not innocent.
I've never been innocent.

973
01:00:33,897 --> 01:00:36,216
What about this man
who killed Colin?

974
01:00:36,217 --> 01:00:38,535
Maybe he's trying
to get revenge.

975
01:00:38,536 --> 01:00:39,861
I don't think so.

976
01:00:41,692 --> 01:00:43,557
They hanged him last year.

977
01:00:45,189 --> 01:00:47,892
People always think
they're better than me...

978
01:00:47,893 --> 01:00:48,874
and they are.

979
01:00:49,293 --> 01:00:50,471
We're just the same.

980
01:00:50,472 --> 01:00:52,206
No, we're not the same.

981
01:00:52,697 --> 01:00:54,447
Buy a plane ticket
back to America.

982
01:00:54,448 --> 01:00:54,790
Why?

983
01:00:57,219 --> 01:01:00,492
Because really bad things
are going to happen.

984
01:01:01,863 --> 01:01:02,674
"Be lucky."

985
01:01:06,092 --> 01:01:09,830
Frank gave it to me
when I graduated police college.

986
01:01:10,008 --> 01:01:11,505
Well, a truck
ran over it.

987
01:01:11,506 --> 01:01:13,826
It's never been
the same since.

988
01:01:17,521 --> 01:01:18,500
What's wrong?

989
01:01:19,239 --> 01:01:20,280
You all right?

990
01:01:21,561 --> 01:01:22,202
Angeline?

991
01:01:22,866 --> 01:01:23,626
Angeline...

992
01:01:25,316 --> 01:01:25,954
Angeline!

993
01:01:30,059 --> 01:01:30,866
Oh, Christ.

994
01:01:31,109 --> 01:01:32,569
You're a sick bastard.

995
01:01:33,570 --> 01:01:36,944
What were you doing here?
Screwing her like last night?

996
01:01:36,945 --> 01:01:38,087
You're in it together,
aren't you?

997
01:01:38,088 --> 01:01:38,899
Yeah, sure.

998
01:01:39,584 --> 01:01:40,539
I want a confession.

999
01:01:40,540 --> 01:01:41,490
All right, I confess.

1000
01:01:41,491 --> 01:01:42,889
You witness that, Paul?

1001
01:01:42,890 --> 01:01:44,295
No, this isn't right,
we don't--

1002
01:01:44,296 --> 01:01:44,862
No, no.

1003
01:01:45,504 --> 01:01:47,511
Oh, come on, then, beat me up.

1004
01:01:47,512 --> 01:01:50,766
Yeah. Let's do this one
for Colin, shall we?

1005
01:02:08,218 --> 01:02:10,511
What do you want me to say?
I'll tell you anything.

1006
01:02:10,512 --> 01:02:12,125
I can't go to prison.

1007
01:02:12,487 --> 01:02:14,218
I can't go to prison...

1008
01:02:17,516 --> 01:02:19,910
You planned it all
with Angeline,

1009
01:02:20,126 --> 01:02:20,985
didn't you?

1010
01:02:21,141 --> 01:02:22,061
You told her

1011
01:02:22,416 --> 01:02:24,386
the moment Stasio
changed his will--

1012
01:02:24,387 --> 01:02:26,483
Yeah, I told her,
but I swear

1013
01:02:26,484 --> 01:02:29,447
I didn't have any idea
what was going to happen.

1014
01:02:29,448 --> 01:02:32,473
But you know who murdered him,
don't you?

1015
01:02:33,583 --> 01:02:36,027
Yeah, it was Angeline,
wasn't it?

1016
01:02:36,956 --> 01:02:38,245
[TELEPHONE RINGING]

1017
01:02:39,087 --> 01:02:41,350
I don't want any calls!
Look--

1018
01:02:41,918 --> 01:02:42,788
Tony? Where?

1019
01:02:46,693 --> 01:02:48,324
All right.
Wait there.

1020
01:02:50,671 --> 01:02:51,831
Just wait there.

1021
01:02:52,580 --> 01:02:53,570
Right, listen,

1022
01:02:54,007 --> 01:02:55,634
Go to your office now,

1023
01:02:56,208 --> 01:02:57,477
get the old will,

1024
01:02:57,479 --> 01:02:59,515
get the files on the
Stasio family, all the letters.

1025
01:02:59,516 --> 01:03:01,010
I want the notes
on all the meetings,

1026
01:03:01,011 --> 01:03:03,018
I want everything,
all right?

1027
01:03:03,019 --> 01:03:04,260
Don't you cheat me.

1028
01:03:04,261 --> 01:03:05,019
Everything.

1029
01:03:05,912 --> 01:03:08,466
I'll join you there
in 20 minutes.

1030
01:03:09,096 --> 01:03:10,505
[FIREWORKS EXPLODING]

1031
01:03:34,646 --> 01:03:36,449
Sorry.
I'm sorry, Frank.

1032
01:03:37,158 --> 01:03:38,789
What the hell happened?

1033
01:03:39,355 --> 01:03:39,757
Ah...

1034
01:03:43,206 --> 01:03:45,056
Oh, I walked into a door.

1035
01:03:46,548 --> 01:03:48,748
It kicked the shit
out of me.

1036
01:03:51,127 --> 01:03:52,338
What's so funny?

1037
01:03:52,592 --> 01:03:53,802
I've cracked it.

1038
01:03:54,532 --> 01:03:57,273
Roscoe is ready
to tell us everything.

1039
01:04:12,928 --> 01:04:15,149
Ten, nine, eight,
seven, six...

1040
01:04:16,616 --> 01:04:17,370
Hey, Tony,

1041
01:04:18,367 --> 01:04:20,810
enjoy the last
of the old decade.

1042
01:04:24,158 --> 01:04:25,794
Happy New Year, Roscoe.

1043
01:04:27,624 --> 01:04:27,906
No!

1044
01:04:39,369 --> 01:04:41,771
[SINGING "AULD LANG SYNE"
OUTSIDE]

1045
01:04:49,184 --> 01:04:50,997
Frank, come on,
let's call somebody,

1046
01:04:50,998 --> 01:04:52,148
for God's sake.

1047
01:04:56,818 --> 01:04:57,969
There's a note.

1048
01:04:59,749 --> 01:05:01,069
He's left a note.

1049
01:05:03,724 --> 01:05:04,185
Hey...

1050
01:05:08,403 --> 01:05:10,149
Just help me turn him over,
will you?

1051
01:05:10,150 --> 01:05:10,783
Come on.

1052
01:05:16,992 --> 01:05:17,622
Oh, God.

1053
01:05:18,233 --> 01:05:20,085
What's that?
Pick it up.

1054
01:05:24,978 --> 01:05:26,072
What's it say?

1055
01:05:27,207 --> 01:05:28,937
Come on, what's it say?

1056
01:05:31,596 --> 01:05:32,001
Tony?

1057
01:05:47,482 --> 01:05:49,194
What is your current profession?

1058
01:05:49,194 --> 01:05:50,936
I'm a private detective.

1059
01:05:51,263 --> 01:05:53,173
And what does the majority
of your work consist of?

1060
01:05:53,174 --> 01:05:53,925
It varies.

1061
01:05:55,528 --> 01:05:57,659
Well, I understand
you have a speciality.

1062
01:05:57,660 --> 01:05:59,695
Well, I do a lot
of matrimonial work.

1063
01:05:59,695 --> 01:06:01,220
You falsify adulteries

1064
01:06:01,731 --> 01:06:03,641
to enable people
to get divorces.

1065
01:06:03,642 --> 01:06:05,263
I like to think
I help unhappy people

1066
01:06:05,264 --> 01:06:06,408
to put their lives
back together.

1067
01:06:06,409 --> 01:06:08,795
You make it sound
like a charity.

1068
01:06:08,796 --> 01:06:10,701
Of course, it isn't a charity,
is it, Mr. Aaron?

1069
01:06:10,702 --> 01:06:12,867
You make money out of
other people's misery.

1070
01:06:12,868 --> 01:06:15,092
What, like barristers, you mean?

1071
01:06:15,954 --> 01:06:17,347
As I understand it,

1072
01:06:17,930 --> 01:06:19,012
You would
make your wife

1073
01:06:19,013 --> 01:06:20,925
go to bed
with these men,

1074
01:06:20,954 --> 01:06:22,096
and then you'd
go to court

1075
01:06:22,098 --> 01:06:23,620
and testify to witnessing
their adultery,

1076
01:06:23,621 --> 01:06:25,149
is that more or less
what you did?

1077
01:06:25,150 --> 01:06:26,101
More or less.

1078
01:06:26,102 --> 01:06:27,855
And how many,
approximately,

1079
01:06:27,856 --> 01:06:28,666
of these...

1080
01:06:28,812 --> 01:06:30,973
dirty weekends did you arrange?

1081
01:06:31,705 --> 01:06:33,847
I don't know, a dozen, maybe?

1082
01:06:35,111 --> 01:06:36,064
Yes, well,
let's not argue

1083
01:06:36,064 --> 01:06:37,975
with that figure
for the moment, a dozen.

1084
01:06:37,976 --> 01:06:40,418
So on at least
a dozen occasions,

1085
01:06:40,775 --> 01:06:42,843
you went to court... and lied.

1086
01:06:42,844 --> 01:06:44,881
And you lied
and you lied again--

1087
01:06:44,882 --> 01:06:45,344
Well--

1088
01:06:45,803 --> 01:06:46,752
It doesn't inspire
much confidence

1089
01:06:46,753 --> 01:06:47,903
in you telling
the truth now,

1090
01:06:47,904 --> 01:06:49,293
does it, Mr. Aaron?

1091
01:06:51,845 --> 01:06:53,628
Why did you leave
the police force?

1092
01:06:53,629 --> 01:06:54,148
Well...

1093
01:06:56,275 --> 01:06:57,433
Well, a friend--

1094
01:06:57,892 --> 01:07:00,745
a friend of mine
was killed, and, um...

1095
01:07:04,990 --> 01:07:06,441
And what, Mr. Aaron?

1096
01:07:08,903 --> 01:07:11,004
I couldn't take the pressure,
I had to leave.

1097
01:07:11,005 --> 01:07:12,914
Isn't it the case
that you were told to resign

1098
01:07:12,915 --> 01:07:15,234
in return for formal charges
being dropped against you?

1099
01:07:15,235 --> 01:07:16,760
That's enough,
Mr. Jenkins.

1100
01:07:16,761 --> 01:07:19,435
The jury will ignore
that last remark.

1101
01:07:19,436 --> 01:07:20,309
Mr. Aaron...

1102
01:07:21,726 --> 01:07:23,351
Why did you marry your wife?

1103
01:07:23,352 --> 01:07:25,386
What do you mean?
That's a stupid question.

1104
01:07:25,387 --> 01:07:27,903
Well, stupid or not,
why did you marry your wife?

1105
01:07:27,904 --> 01:07:30,637
The same reason everybody does,
because I loved her.

1106
01:07:30,638 --> 01:07:33,134
I don't believe
that's the truth.

1107
01:07:33,342 --> 01:07:35,724
Tony bought a car off me
a couple of years ago,

1108
01:07:35,725 --> 01:07:37,579
and we got to be friends.

1109
01:07:37,959 --> 01:07:40,532
He was seeing this married woman
at the time, you know.

1110
01:07:40,533 --> 01:07:41,832
This was
Hazel Powers?

1111
01:07:41,834 --> 01:07:43,013
Yeah, that's right.

1112
01:07:43,014 --> 01:07:44,446
Then a copper
was killed by Powers,

1113
01:07:44,447 --> 01:07:46,541
and he was... tried and hung.

1114
01:07:48,201 --> 01:07:50,180
Anyway, Tony and I
were drinking one night,

1115
01:07:50,181 --> 01:07:52,275
and he said he was going
to marry Hazel, you know.

1116
01:07:52,276 --> 01:07:53,544
I couldn't believe it,

1117
01:07:53,545 --> 01:07:54,692
because
all he'd ever said before

1118
01:07:54,694 --> 01:07:56,287
was she was just a good...

1119
01:07:55,287 --> 01:07:55,625
Yes?

1120
01:07:58,084 --> 01:07:59,009
Good in bed.

1121
01:08:02,139 --> 01:08:03,242
I never thought

1122
01:08:03,728 --> 01:08:05,316
he really cared
about her.

1123
01:08:05,317 --> 01:08:07,040
I said this to him,
and he just laughed.

1124
01:08:07,041 --> 01:08:08,755
He said, "Have you
seen her house?

1125
01:08:08,756 --> 01:08:10,475
Do you know how much
money she's got?"

1126
01:08:10,476 --> 01:08:13,115
He didn't leave much doubt
about why he was marrying her.

1127
01:08:13,116 --> 01:08:16,621
Did you see Mr. Aaron
subsequent to the marriage.

1128
01:08:17,160 --> 01:08:18,553
After they got married,

1129
01:08:18,554 --> 01:08:19,765
Tony found out
this guy, Powers,

1130
01:08:19,766 --> 01:08:20,871
had huge debts.

1131
01:08:21,231 --> 01:08:22,663
He was virtually
bankrupt.

1132
01:08:22,664 --> 01:08:25,113
His club was sold,
his house was put on the market,

1133
01:08:25,114 --> 01:08:27,499
and Hazel didn't end up
with anything at all.

1134
01:08:27,500 --> 01:08:30,172
He was really mad
when he found out.

1135
01:08:30,965 --> 01:08:33,511
He said he'd made
the biggest mistake of his life.

1136
01:08:33,512 --> 01:08:35,202
Mr. Aaron,
were you aware

1137
01:08:35,203 --> 01:08:37,140
that your wife had
an insurance policy

1138
01:08:37,141 --> 01:08:38,222
through the access
trades union

1139
01:08:38,223 --> 01:08:39,367
of which
she was a member?

1140
01:08:39,369 --> 01:08:39,651
No.

1141
01:08:40,959 --> 01:08:41,944
Well, I wasn't

1142
01:08:41,945 --> 01:08:43,282
until I went through
her things after--

1143
01:08:43,283 --> 01:08:45,600
Do you recall
the conditions of the policy?

1144
01:08:45,601 --> 01:08:47,677
I just read it
through once.

1145
01:08:47,678 --> 01:08:49,011
You stood to gain
a thousand pounds

1146
01:08:49,012 --> 01:08:50,343
in the event
of her death.

1147
01:08:50,344 --> 01:08:51,395
Look, it's a standard
insurance policy--

1148
01:08:51,396 --> 01:08:52,921
Thank you, Mr. Aaron,
that's all for now.

1149
01:08:52,922 --> 01:08:55,091
I can say
with complete confidence

1150
01:08:55,092 --> 01:08:57,124
that this is the gun
that killed them both.

1151
01:08:57,125 --> 01:08:59,909
We asked him twice
if he owned a gun.

1152
01:09:01,104 --> 01:09:02,844
He denied it both times.

1153
01:09:02,882 --> 01:09:04,156
Is this your gun?

1154
01:09:04,763 --> 01:09:07,432
I said, is this your gun,
Mr. Aaron?

1155
01:09:10,012 --> 01:09:11,312
It looks like my gun.

1156
01:09:11,313 --> 01:09:13,892
How did it come to be
in the boiler room of the hotel?

1157
01:09:13,893 --> 01:09:15,514
It was stolen from me.

1158
01:09:15,745 --> 01:09:17,076
I had a break-in in my office.

1159
01:09:17,077 --> 01:09:19,336
Really? And when did you
report it stolen?

1160
01:09:19,337 --> 01:09:21,275
I didn't know anything
was missing at the time.

1161
01:09:21,276 --> 01:09:22,930
I didn't realize
until after the murders.

1162
01:09:23,531 --> 01:09:26,329
And were there any witnesses
to this alleged break-in?

1163
01:09:26,330 --> 01:09:28,968
Yes, the client I was helping.
He was with me.

1164
01:09:28,969 --> 01:09:30,178
Who is this man?

1165
01:09:30,561 --> 01:09:31,801
He's a barrister.

1166
01:09:31,802 --> 01:09:33,805
Oh, and, uh,
we'll get a chance to talk

1167
01:09:33,806 --> 01:09:35,013
to this
barrister, will we?

1168
01:09:35,014 --> 01:09:36,668
He doesn't want
to appear in court.
Really?

1169
01:09:36,669 --> 01:09:38,391
Well, that'll be the first
barrister I've ever known

1170
01:09:38,392 --> 01:09:39,821
to be shy of appearing in court.

1171
01:09:39,822 --> 01:09:42,265
So really,
what you're telling us

1172
01:09:42,301 --> 01:09:43,606
is that no one
can substantiate

1173
01:09:43,607 --> 01:09:44,848
this alleged break-in?

1174
01:09:44,849 --> 01:09:46,251
Yes, this barrister can.

1175
01:09:46,252 --> 01:09:47,119
Yes, well...

1176
01:09:50,860 --> 01:09:52,359
Why did you have a gun?

1177
01:09:52,360 --> 01:09:54,015
I mean,
did you, uh...

1178
01:09:54,016 --> 01:09:55,350
did you use it
to threaten people?

1179
01:09:55,351 --> 01:09:57,286
Really, My Lord, I must object.

1180
01:09:57,287 --> 01:09:58,244
I'm just trying
to understand.

1181
01:09:58,245 --> 01:09:59,486
I mean, why did you have a gun?

1182
01:09:59,487 --> 01:10:01,839
I don't know,
I just kept it, that's all.

1183
01:10:01,840 --> 01:10:05,443
And when did you apply
for a license for the gun?

1184
01:10:08,078 --> 01:10:10,389
I didn't have a license for it.

1185
01:10:11,342 --> 01:10:12,899
We've got to get
that barrister to talk.

1186
01:10:12,900 --> 01:10:14,573
He won't.
I've tried.

1187
01:10:18,724 --> 01:10:21,335
The beretta was fired
three times in all

1188
01:10:21,336 --> 01:10:23,719
from a distance
of less than four feet,

1189
01:10:23,720 --> 01:10:25,119
using one of
the bedroom pillows

1190
01:10:25,120 --> 01:10:26,571
to muffle the noise.

1191
01:10:26,744 --> 01:10:27,855
Stasio was hit twice...

1192
01:10:27,856 --> 01:10:29,248
Give this to Frank.

1193
01:10:30,023 --> 01:10:32,251
The first bullet penetrated
his chest and his heart,

1194
01:10:32,252 --> 01:10:34,378
and in all probability,
he was already dead

1195
01:10:34,379 --> 01:10:36,654
when the second shot
was fired.

1196
01:10:41,284 --> 01:10:42,747
You've made yourself
hard to meet.

1197
01:10:42,748 --> 01:10:43,959
Look, I'm afraid

1198
01:10:44,020 --> 01:10:45,739
you're wasting
your time, Detective.

1199
01:10:45,740 --> 01:10:47,361
I've already told you
I have nothing to--

1200
01:10:47,362 --> 01:10:49,935
Is he telling the truth
about the break-in?

1201
01:10:49,936 --> 01:10:51,278
Look, I can't help you,
I'm afraid.

1202
01:10:51,279 --> 01:10:52,227
My reputation is--

1203
01:10:52,228 --> 01:10:53,346
Sod your reputation.

1204
01:10:53,347 --> 01:10:55,148
Is he telling
the truth?

1205
01:10:55,318 --> 01:10:58,933
I have nothing to say.
Now, please leave me alone.

1206
01:11:07,058 --> 01:11:08,622
Is there room for me?

1207
01:11:10,590 --> 01:11:11,863
Look, I'd like
to remind you

1208
01:11:11,864 --> 01:11:13,316
who I am, Detective.

1209
01:11:13,708 --> 01:11:15,241
I'm not going
to be bullied--

1210
01:11:15,242 --> 01:11:17,368
I'm not giving you a choice.
This is a man's life,

1211
01:11:17,369 --> 01:11:19,278
or do you want me to
tell your fancy friends

1212
01:11:19,279 --> 01:11:20,963
what kind of person you are?

1213
01:11:20,964 --> 01:11:22,070
This your coat?

1214
01:11:23,638 --> 01:11:25,611
I had paid Mr. Aaron to arrange

1215
01:11:25,612 --> 01:11:27,898
for myself and a woman
to be photographed together

1216
01:11:27,899 --> 01:11:30,174
to help me...
obtain a divorce.

1217
01:11:32,073 --> 01:11:33,277
He met me at Brighton station,

1218
01:11:33,278 --> 01:11:34,805
and then we went back
to his office

1219
01:11:34,806 --> 01:11:36,259
to sign some papers.

1220
01:11:37,034 --> 01:11:38,624
I immediately noticed
something was wrong,

1221
01:11:38,625 --> 01:11:40,629
the door had been forced open.

1222
01:11:40,630 --> 01:11:43,603
Mr. Aaron checked
in his desk and around,

1223
01:11:43,648 --> 01:11:45,368
but couldn't see anything
missing at the time,

1224
01:11:45,369 --> 01:11:47,064
and we continued with...

1225
01:11:47,568 --> 01:11:48,850
with our business.

1226
01:11:48,932 --> 01:11:51,447
But there were
definite signs of a break-in?

1227
01:11:51,448 --> 01:11:52,961
Yes. Yes, there were.

1228
01:11:54,567 --> 01:11:56,220
You're part
of the prosecution.

1229
01:11:56,221 --> 01:11:57,272
I'm still
not certain--

1230
01:11:57,273 --> 01:12:00,016
You're part of
the prosecution, Frank!

1231
01:12:00,645 --> 01:12:01,791
You can't go
looking for evidence

1232
01:12:01,792 --> 01:12:03,285
for the bloody defense.

1233
01:12:03,286 --> 01:12:04,849
I'm not sure anymore.

1234
01:12:05,069 --> 01:12:07,806
You've got the gun.
What more do you want?

1235
01:12:07,807 --> 01:12:08,791
You know he did it,

1236
01:12:08,792 --> 01:12:11,345
you just don't want
to believe it.

1237
01:12:12,066 --> 01:12:13,658
Waterston knows something.

1238
01:12:13,659 --> 01:12:14,806
What's he got up his sleeve?

1239
01:12:14,807 --> 01:12:16,932
I mean, there's the gun, yes.

1240
01:12:16,933 --> 01:12:18,336
Even the suicide note.

1241
01:12:18,337 --> 01:12:20,373
They're damning,
but they're circumstantial.

1242
01:12:20,374 --> 01:12:22,029
Nothing directly connects you.

1243
01:12:22,030 --> 01:12:23,897
There are
no eyewitnesses,

1244
01:12:24,222 --> 01:12:25,751
so he's got to have
something more.

1245
01:12:25,752 --> 01:12:27,903
But there isn't anything more.

1246
01:12:31,573 --> 01:12:33,766
I went to the hotel that night
to wait for Carlo.

1247
01:12:33,767 --> 01:12:36,791
I was going to drive him home
after the, uh...

1248
01:12:36,792 --> 01:12:37,843
the photograph.

1249
01:12:38,446 --> 01:12:40,994
I was there for about half
an hour when I saw something.

1250
01:12:40,995 --> 01:12:42,139
What did you see?

1251
01:12:42,141 --> 01:12:43,122
I saw someone

1252
01:12:43,188 --> 01:12:45,352
climb over the roof
of the hotel,

1253
01:12:45,353 --> 01:12:46,752
they stopped for a moment,

1254
01:12:46,753 --> 01:12:48,628
and then they climbed
into a window.

1255
01:12:48,629 --> 01:12:49,900
That's the kitchen window,

1256
01:12:49,901 --> 01:12:51,811
that's the third
floor window

1257
01:12:51,812 --> 01:12:53,716
at the front
of the hotel.

1258
01:12:53,717 --> 01:12:54,061
Yes.

1259
01:12:56,491 --> 01:12:58,220
Did you see who it was?

1260
01:12:59,068 --> 01:13:01,067
It was definitely a man,
from their clothes,

1261
01:13:01,068 --> 01:13:02,279
but it was dark.

1262
01:13:02,280 --> 01:13:03,550
I couldn't see
them very well.

1263
01:13:03,551 --> 01:13:05,462
So you have no idea
who it might have been?

1264
01:13:05,463 --> 01:13:07,376
I know exactly who it was.

1265
01:13:07,943 --> 01:13:11,097
You say it was dark,
how can you be so sure?

1266
01:13:11,098 --> 01:13:12,873
Before they went back
inside the hotel,

1267
01:13:12,874 --> 01:13:15,072
they stopped
to light a cigarette.

1268
01:13:15,073 --> 01:13:16,660
Did you see their face
in the light?

1269
01:13:16,661 --> 01:13:17,774
At that distance?

1270
01:13:17,775 --> 01:13:18,528
No, but...

1271
01:13:20,540 --> 01:13:24,014
they had a lighter,
and it didn't work properly,

1272
01:13:24,015 --> 01:13:26,694
so they tapped it
against their hand,

1273
01:13:26,779 --> 01:13:28,530
and then
they shook it twice,

1274
01:13:28,531 --> 01:13:30,505
and then tried to light it.

1275
01:13:31,173 --> 01:13:31,864
It was...

1276
01:13:32,600 --> 01:13:35,661
such an individual way
of lighting a cigarette.

1277
01:13:35,662 --> 01:13:37,282
I forgot all about it,

1278
01:13:37,663 --> 01:13:39,065
until I saw Tony Aaron

1279
01:13:39,066 --> 01:13:40,302
do exactly the same thing
with his lighter.

1280
01:13:40,303 --> 01:13:42,628
Liar! She's a liar!
She's making it up!

1281
01:13:42,629 --> 01:13:44,079
Sit down, Mr. Aaron.

1282
01:14:05,158 --> 01:14:08,211
What did she buy,
the woman who was just in here?

1283
01:14:08,212 --> 01:14:10,251
An aeroplane ticket for America.

1284
01:14:10,251 --> 01:14:11,392
Why do you want to know?

1285
01:14:11,393 --> 01:14:12,496
One-way ticket?

1286
01:14:12,983 --> 01:14:13,327
Yes.

1287
01:14:18,134 --> 01:14:20,047
You have seen the evidence.

1288
01:14:22,439 --> 01:14:24,755
The solicitor's letter,
the gun.

1289
01:14:27,591 --> 01:14:31,078
You've seen the shocking
photographs of the dead.

1290
01:14:31,295 --> 01:14:33,267
Now, you must be thinking...

1291
01:14:33,566 --> 01:14:35,658
what kind of a person
could commit this atrocity.

1292
01:14:35,659 --> 01:14:38,377
A man thrown out
of the police force,

1293
01:14:39,802 --> 01:14:41,225
who, by his
own confession,

1294
01:14:41,226 --> 01:14:43,724
now makes his living
by fraud and deception.

1295
01:14:43,725 --> 01:14:46,446
A man who has perjured himself
regularly in court

1296
01:14:46,447 --> 01:14:48,119
for the past two years.

1297
01:14:48,310 --> 01:14:50,274
A man who was
desperate for money,

1298
01:14:50,274 --> 01:14:51,944
and I suggest to you...

1299
01:14:52,330 --> 01:14:55,106
was prepared to do
anything to get it.

1300
01:14:56,881 --> 01:14:58,847
I-- I know things look bad,

1301
01:14:59,347 --> 01:15:02,406
and I'm no angel,
I've done things wrong,

1302
01:15:03,844 --> 01:15:05,446
but I didn't do this.

1303
01:15:06,314 --> 01:15:08,429
Somebody stole my gun
and tried to frame me.

1304
01:15:08,430 --> 01:15:09,935
That's what happened.

1305
01:15:11,304 --> 01:15:13,014
Why should I kill my wife?

1306
01:15:13,015 --> 01:15:15,445
I mean,
I could just divorce her.

1307
01:15:16,367 --> 01:15:17,952
I mean,
what they're saying--

1308
01:15:17,953 --> 01:15:20,573
They're saying I killed my wife
for a thousand pounds,

1309
01:15:20,574 --> 01:15:21,969
and then killed
this man as well,

1310
01:15:21,970 --> 01:15:24,517
so that people
wouldn't suspect me?

1311
01:15:24,686 --> 01:15:26,003
It's sick. It's--

1312
01:15:28,043 --> 01:15:30,470
I couldn't do anything
like that.

1313
01:15:30,859 --> 01:15:32,309
I don't deny I've lied.

1314
01:15:32,310 --> 01:15:34,584
I've done a lot of things
wrong in my life,

1315
01:15:34,585 --> 01:15:35,564
but not this.

